  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Family of Elkanah'
      title: The Family of Elkanah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now there was a certain man of Ramathaim Zophim, of the mountains
        of Ephraim, and his name was  Elkanah the son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu,
        the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephraimite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he had two wives: the name of one was Hannah, and the name of
        the other Peninnah. Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'This man went up from his city yearly to worship and sacrifice to
        the Lord of hosts in Shiloh. Also the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas,
        the priests of the Lord, were there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And whenever the time came for Elkanah to make an offering, he would
        give portions to Peninnah his wife and to all her sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But to Hannah he would give a double portion, for he loved Hannah,
        although the Lord had closed her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And her rival also provoked her severely, to make her miserable,
        because the Lord had closed her womb. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Hannah\u2019s Vow"
      title: "Hannah\u2019s Vow"
      number: 7
      content: So it was, year by year, when she went up to the house of the Lord,
        that she provoked her; therefore she wept and did not eat.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Elkanah her husband said to her, \u201CHannah, why do you weep?
        Why do you not eat? And why is your heart grieved? Am I not better to you
        than ten sons?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Hannah arose after they had finished eating and drinking in Shiloh.
        Now Eli the priest was sitting on the seat by the doorpost of the tabernacle
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And she was in bitterness of soul, and prayed to the Lord and wept
        in anguish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then she made a vow and said, \u201CO Lord of hosts, if You will
        indeed look on the affliction of Your maidservant and remember me, and not
        forget Your maidservant, but will give Your maidservant a male child, then
        I will give him to the Lord all the days of his life, and no razor shall
        come upon his head.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And it happened, as she continued praying before the Lord, that Eli
        watched her mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now Hannah spoke in her heart; only her lips moved, but her voice
        was not heard. Therefore Eli thought she was drunk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Eli said to her, \u201CHow long will you be drunk? Put your wine
        away from you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Hannah answered and said, \u201CNo, my lord, I am a woman of
        sorrowful spirit. I have drunk neither wine nor intoxicating drink, but have
        poured out my soul before the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CDo not consider your maidservant a wicked woman, for out of
        the abundance of my complaint and grief I have spoken until now.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Eli answered and said, \u201CGo in peace, and the God of Israel
        grant your petition which you have asked of Him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Samuel Is Born and Dedicated'
      title: Samuel Is Born and Dedicated
      number: 18
      content: "And she said, \u201CLet your maidservant find favor in your sight.\u201D
        So the woman went her way and ate, and her face was no longer sad."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then they rose early in the morning and worshiped before the Lord,
        and returned and came to their house at Ramah. And Elkanah knew Hannah his
        wife, and the Lord  remembered her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So it came to pass in the process of time that Hannah conceived and
        bore a son, and called his name Samuel, saying, \u201CBecause I have asked
        for him from the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the man Elkanah and all his house went up to offer to the Lord
        the yearly sacrifice and his vow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Hannah did not go up, for she said to her husband, \u201CNot
        until the child is weaned; then I will take him, that he may appear before
        the Lord and remain there forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Elkanah her husband said to her, \u201CDo what seems best to you;
        wait until you have weaned him. Only let the Lord establish His word.\u201D
        Then the woman stayed and nursed her son until she had weaned him."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now when she had weaned him, she took him up with her, with three
        bulls, one ephah of flour, and a skin of wine, and brought him to the house
        of the Lord in Shiloh. And the child was young. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then they slaughtered a bull, and brought the child to Eli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And she said, \u201CO my lord! As your soul lives, my lord, I am
        the woman who stood by you here, praying to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For this child I prayed, and the Lord has granted me my petition
        which I asked of Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore I also have lent him to the Lord; as long as he lives he
        shall be lent to the Lord.\u201D So they worshiped the Lord there."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hannah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Hannah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 1
      content: "And Hannah prayed and said:\u201CMy heart rejoices in the Lord;My
        horn is exalted in the Lord.I smile at my enemies,Because I rejoice in Your
        salvation."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNo one is holy like the Lord,For there  is  none besides You,Nor
        is  there any rock like our God."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CTalk no more so very proudly;Let no arrogance come from your
        mouth,For the Lord  is the God of knowledge;And by Him actions are weighed."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThe bows of the mighty men are broken,And those who stumbled
        are girded with strength."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Those  who  were full have hired themselves out for bread,And the
        hungry have ceased to  hunger.Even the barren has borne seven,And she who
        has many children has become feeble.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThe  Lord kills and makes alive;He brings down to the grave
        and brings up."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The Lord  makes poor and makes rich;He brings low and lifts up.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "He raises the poor from the dustAnd lifts the beggar from the ash
        heap,To set them among princesAnd make them inherit the throne of glory.\u201CFor
        the pillars of the earth are the Lord\u2019s,And He has set the world upon
        them."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He will guard the feet of His saints,But the wicked shall be silent
        in darkness.\u201CFor by strength no man shall prevail."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The adversaries of the Lord shall be broken in pieces;From heaven
        He will thunder against them.The Lord will judge the ends of the earth.\u201CHe
        will give strength to His king,And exalt the horn of His anointed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Wicked Sons of Eli'
      title: The Wicked Sons of Eli
      number: 11
      content: Then Elkanah went to his house at Ramah. But the child ministered
        to the Lord before Eli the priest.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the sons of Eli were  corrupt; they did not know the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the priests\u2019 custom with the people was  that when any man
        offered a sacrifice, the priest\u2019s servant would come with a three-pronged
        fleshhook in his hand while the meat was boiling. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then he would thrust it into the pan, or kettle, or caldron, or pot;
        and the priest would take for himself all that the fleshhook brought up.
        So they did in Shiloh to all the Israelites who came there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Also, before they burned the fat, the priest\u2019s servant would
        come and say to the man who sacrificed, \u201CGive meat for roasting to the
        priest, for he will not take boiled meat from you, but raw.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And if the man said to him, \u201CThey should really burn the fat
        first; then you may take as  much as your heart desires,\u201D he would then
        answer him, \u201CNo, but you must give it now; and if not, I will take it
        by force.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Samuel\u2019s Childhood Ministry"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s Childhood Ministry"
      number: 17
      content: Therefore the sin of the young men was very great before the Lord,
        for men abhorred the offering of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But Samuel ministered before the Lord, even  as a child, wearing
        a linen ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Moreover his mother used to make him a little robe, and bring it
        to him year by year when she came up with her husband to offer the yearly
        sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Eli would bless Elkanah and his wife, and say, \u201CThe Lord
        give you descendants from this woman for the loan that was given to the Lord.\u201D
        Then they would go to their own home."
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Prophecy Against Eli\u2019s Household"
      title: "Prophecy Against Eli\u2019s Household"
      number: 21
      content: And the Lord  visited Hannah, so that she conceived and bore three
        sons and two daughters. Meanwhile the child Samuel grew before the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now Eli was very old; and he heard everything his sons did to all
        Israel, and how they lay with the women who assembled at the door of the
        tabernacle of meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So he said to them, \u201CWhy do you do such things? For I hear of
        your evil dealings from all the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "No, my sons! For it  is not a good report that I hear. You make the
        Lord\u2019s people transgress. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If one man sins against another, God will judge him. But if a man
        sins against the Lord, who will intercede for him?\u201D Nevertheless they
        did not heed the voice of their father, because the Lord desired to kill
        them."
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And the child Samuel grew in stature, and in favor both with the Lord
        and men.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then a man of God came to Eli and said to him, \u201CThus says the
        Lord: \u2018Did I not clearly reveal Myself to the house of your father when
        they were in Egypt in Pharaoh\u2019s house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Did I not choose him out of all the tribes of Israel to  be My priest,
        to offer upon My altar, to burn incense, and to wear an ephod before Me?
        And did I not give to the house of your father all the offerings of the children
        of Israel made by fire? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Why do you kick at My sacrifice and My offering which I have commanded
        in  My  dwelling place, and honor your sons more than Me, to make yourselves
        fat with the best of all the offerings of Israel My people?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore the Lord God of Israel says: \u2018I said indeed that your
        house and the house of your father would walk before Me forever.\u2019 But
        now the Lord says: \u2018Far be it from Me; for those who honor Me I will
        honor, and those who despise Me shall be lightly esteemed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Behold, the days are coming that I will cut off your arm and the
        arm of your father\u2019s house, so that there will not be an old man in
        your house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And you will see an enemy in  My dwelling place, despite all the
        good which God does for Israel. And there shall not be an old man in your
        house forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'But any of your men whom I do not cut off from My altar shall consume
        your eyes and grieve your heart. And all the descendants of your house shall
        die in the flower of their age. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now this shall  be  a sign to you that will come upon your two sons,
        on Hophni and Phinehas: in one day they shall die, both of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then I will raise up for Myself a faithful priest who shall do according
        to what is in My heart and in My mind. I will build him a sure house, and
        he shall walk before My anointed forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And it shall come to pass that everyone who is left in your house
        will come and bow down to him for a piece of silver and a morsel of bread,
        and say, \u201CPlease, put me in one of the priestly positions, that I may
        eat a piece of bread.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samuel\u2019s First Prophecy"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s First Prophecy"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the boy Samuel ministered to the Lord before Eli. And the word
        of the Lord was rare in those days; there  was no widespread revelation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it came to pass at that time, while Eli was lying down in his
        place, and when his eyes had begun to grow so dim that he could not see, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and before the lamp of God went out in the tabernacle of the Lord
        where the ark of God was, and while Samuel was lying down, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "that the Lord called Samuel. And he answered, \u201CHere I am!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he ran to Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, for you called me.\u201DAnd
        he said, \u201CI did not call; lie down again.\u201D And he went and lay
        down."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the Lord called yet again, \u201CSamuel!\u201DSo Samuel arose
        and went to Eli, and said, \u201CHere I am, for you called me.\u201D He answered,
        \u201CI did not call, my son; lie down again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: (Now Samuel did not yet know the Lord, nor was the word of the Lord
        yet revealed to him.)
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the Lord called Samuel again the third time. So he arose and
        went to Eli, and said, \u201CHere I am, for you did call me.\u201DThen Eli
        perceived that the Lord had called the boy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Therefore Eli said to Samuel, \u201CGo, lie down; and it shall be,
        if He calls you, that you must say, \u2018Speak, Lord, for Your servant hears.\u2019
        \u201D So Samuel went and lay down in his place."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now the Lord came and stood and called as at other times, \u201CSamuel!
        Samuel!\u201DAnd Samuel answered, \u201CSpeak, for Your servant hears.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the Lord said to Samuel: \u201CBehold, I will do something in
        Israel at which both ears of everyone who hears it will tingle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In that day I will perform against Eli all that I have spoken concerning
        his house, from beginning to end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For I have told him that I will judge his house forever for the iniquity
        which he knows, because his sons made themselves vile, and he did not restrain
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And therefore I have sworn to the house of Eli that the iniquity
        of Eli\u2019s house shall not be atoned for by sacrifice or offering forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Samuel lay down until morning, and opened the doors of the house
        of the Lord. And Samuel was afraid to tell Eli the vision. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Eli called Samuel and said, \u201CSamuel, my son!\u201DHe answered,
        \u201CHere I am.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhat is the word that the  Lord spoke to you?
        Please do not hide it from me. God do so to you, and more also, if you hide
        anything from me of all the things that He said to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Samuel told him everything, and hid nothing from him. And he
        said, \u201CIt is the Lord. Let Him do what seems good to Him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Samuel grew, and the Lord was with him and let none of his words
        fall to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And all Israel from Dan to Beersheba knew that Samuel had  been established
        as a prophet of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Then the Lord appeared again in Shiloh. For the Lord revealed Himself
        to Samuel in Shiloh by the word of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark of God Captured'
      title: The Ark of God Captured
      number: 1
      content: 'And the word of Samuel came to all Israel.Now Israel went out to
        battle against the Philistines, and encamped beside Ebenezer; and the Philistines
        encamped in Aphek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then the Philistines put themselves in battle array against Israel.
        And when they joined battle, Israel was defeated by the Philistines, who
        killed about four thousand men of the army in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And when the people had come into the camp, the elders of Israel
        said, \u201CWhy has the Lord defeated us today before the Philistines? Let
        us bring the ark of the covenant of the Lord from Shiloh to us, that when
        it comes among us it may save us from the hand of our enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So the people sent to Shiloh, that they might bring from there the
        ark of the covenant of the Lord of hosts, who dwells between  the cherubim.
        And the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were there with the ark of
        the covenant of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when the ark of the covenant of the Lord came into the camp,
        all Israel shouted so loudly that the earth shook. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now when the Philistines heard the noise of the shout, they said,
        \u201CWhat does the sound of this great shout in the camp of the Hebrews
        mean?\u201D Then they understood that the ark of the Lord had come into the
        camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the Philistines were afraid, for they said, \u201CGod has come
        into the camp!\u201D And they said, \u201CWoe to us! For such a thing has
        never happened before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Woe to us! Who will deliver us from the hand of these mighty gods?
        These are the gods who struck the Egyptians with all the plagues in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Be strong and conduct yourselves like men, you Philistines, that
        you do not become servants of the Hebrews, as they have been to you. Conduct
        yourselves like men, and fight!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the Philistines fought, and Israel was defeated, and every man
        fled to his tent. There was a very great slaughter, and there fell of Israel
        thirty thousand foot soldiers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Death of Eli'
      title: Death of Eli
      number: 11
      content: Also the ark of God was captured; and the two sons of Eli, Hophni
        and Phinehas, died.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then a man of Benjamin ran from the battle line the same day, and
        came to Shiloh with his clothes torn and dirt on his head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when he came, there was Eli, sitting on a seat by the wayside
        watching, for his heart trembled for the ark of God. And when the man came
        into the city and told it, all the city cried out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Eli heard the noise of the outcry, he said, \u201CWhat does
        the sound of this tumult mean?\u201D And the man came quickly and told Eli. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Eli was ninety-eight years old, and his eyes were so dim that he could
        not see.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the man said to Eli, \u201CI am he who came from the battle.
        And I fled today from the battle line.\u201DAnd he said, \u201CWhat happened,
        my son?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So the messenger answered and said, \u201CIsrael has fled before
        the Philistines, and there has been a great slaughter among the people. Also
        your two sons, Hophni and Phinehas, are dead; and the ark of God has been
        captured.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Ichabod'
      title: Ichabod
      number: 18
      content: Then it happened, when he made mention of the ark of God, that Eli
        fell off the seat backward by the side of the gate; and his neck was broken
        and he died, for the man was old and heavy. And he had judged Israel forty
        years.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now his daughter-in-law, Phinehas\u2019s wife, was with child, due
        to be delivered; and when she heard the news that the ark of God was captured,
        and that her father-in-law and her husband were dead, she bowed herself and
        gave birth, for her labor pains came upon her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And about the time of her death the women who stood by her said to
        her, \u201CDo not fear, for you have borne a son.\u201D But she did not answer,
        nor did she regard it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then she named the child Ichabod, saying, \u201CThe glory has departed
        from Israel!\u201D because the ark of God had been captured and because of
        her father-in-law and her husband. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And she said, \u201CThe glory has departed from Israel, for the ark
        of God has been captured.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Philistines and the Ark'
      title: The Philistines and the Ark
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the Philistines took the ark of God and brought it from Ebenezer
        to Ashdod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When the Philistines took the ark of God, they brought it into the
        house of Dagon and set it by Dagon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when the people of Ashdod arose early in the morning, there was
        Dagon, fallen on its face to the earth before the ark of the Lord. So they
        took Dagon and set it in its place again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when they arose early the next morning, there was Dagon, fallen
        on its face to the ground before the ark of the Lord. The head of Dagon and
        both the palms of its hands were broken off on the threshold; only Dagon\u2019s
        torso was left of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Therefore neither the priests of Dagon nor any who come into Dagon\u2019s
        house tread on the threshold of Dagon in Ashdod to this day."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But the hand of the Lord was heavy on the people of Ashdod, and He
        ravaged them and struck them with tumors, both Ashdod and its territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when the men of Ashdod saw how it  was, they said, \u201CThe
        ark of the God of Israel must not remain with us, for His hand is harsh toward
        us and Dagon our god.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore they sent and gathered to themselves all the lords of the
        Philistines, and said, \u201CWhat shall we do with the ark of the God of
        Israel?\u201DAnd they answered, \u201CLet the ark of the God of Israel be
        carried away to Gath.\u201D So they carried the ark of the God of Israel
        away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So it was, after they had carried it away, that the hand of the Lord
        was against the city with a very great destruction; and He struck the men
        of the city, both small and great, and tumors broke out on them.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore they sent the ark of God to Ekron. So it was, as the ark
        of God came to Ekron, that the Ekronites cried out, saying, \u201CThey have
        brought the ark of the God of Israel to us, to kill us and our people!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So they sent and gathered together all the lords of the Philistines,
        and said, \u201CSend away the ark of the God of Israel, and let it go back
        to its own place, so that it does not kill us and our people.\u201D For there
        was a deadly destruction throughout all the city; the hand of God was very
        heavy there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And the men who did not die were stricken with the tumors, and the
        cry of the city went up to heaven.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Returned to Israel'
      title: The Ark Returned to Israel
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the ark of the Lord was in the country of the Philistines seven
        months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Philistines called for the priests and the diviners, saying,
        \u201CWhat shall we do with the ark of the Lord? Tell us how we should send
        it to its place.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So they said, \u201CIf you send away the ark of the God of Israel,
        do not send it empty; but by all means return it to Him with  a trespass
        offering. Then you will be healed, and it will be known to you why His hand
        is not removed from you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then they said, \u201CWhat is the trespass offering which we shall
        return to Him?\u201DThey answered, \u201CFive golden tumors and five golden
        rats, according  to the number of the lords of the Philistines. For the same
        plague was on all of you and on your lords. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore you shall make images of your tumors and images of your
        rats that ravage the land, and you shall give glory to the God of Israel;
        perhaps He will lighten His hand from you, from your gods, and from your
        land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Why then do you harden your hearts as the Egyptians and Pharaoh hardened
        their hearts? When He did mighty things among them, did they not let the
        people go, that they might depart? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now therefore, make a new cart, take two milk cows which have never
        been yoked, and hitch the cows to the cart; and take their calves home, away
        from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then take the ark of the Lord and set it on the cart; and put the
        articles of gold which you are returning to Him as a trespass offering in
        a chest by its side. Then send it away, and let it go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And watch: if it goes up the road to its own territory, to Beth Shemesh,
        then He has done us this great evil. But if not, then we shall know that
        it  is not His hand that struck us\u2014it happened to us by chance.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the men did so; they took two milk cows and hitched them to
        the cart, and shut up their calves at home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they set the ark of the Lord on the cart, and the chest with
        the gold rats and the images of their tumors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Then the cows headed straight for the road to Beth Shemesh, and went
        along the highway, lowing as they went, and did not turn aside to the right
        hand or the left. And the lords of the Philistines went after them to the
        border of Beth Shemesh.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the  people  of Beth Shemesh were reaping their wheat harvest
        in the valley; and they lifted their eyes and saw the ark, and rejoiced to
        see it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the cart came into the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh, and
        stood there; a large stone was there. So they split the wood of the cart
        and offered the cows as a burnt offering to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Levites took down the ark of the Lord and the chest that was
        with it, in which were the articles of gold, and put them on the large stone.
        Then the men of Beth Shemesh offered burnt offerings and made sacrifices
        the same day to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So when the five lords of the Philistines had seen it, they returned
        to Ekron the same day.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'These are the golden tumors which the Philistines returned as a trespass
        offering to the Lord: one for Ashdod, one for Gaza, one for Ashkelon, one
        for Gath, one for Ekron; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: and the golden rats, according  to the number of all the cities of
        the Philistines belonging to the five lords, both fortified cities and country
        villages, even as far as the large stone  of Abel on which they set the ark
        of the Lord, which  stone  remains to this day in the field of Joshua of
        Beth Shemesh.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Ark at Kirjath Jearim'
      title: The Ark at Kirjath Jearim
      number: 19
      content: Then He struck the men of Beth Shemesh, because they had looked into
        the ark of the Lord. He struck fifty thousand and seventy men of the people,
        and the people lamented because the Lord had struck the people with a great
        slaughter.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the men of Beth Shemesh said, \u201CWho is able to stand before
        this holy Lord God? And to whom shall it go up from us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So they sent messengers to the inhabitants of Kirjath Jearim, saying,
        \u201CThe Philistines have brought back the ark of the Lord; come down and
        take it up with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Samuel Judges Israel'
      title: Samuel Judges Israel
      number: 1
      content: Then the men of Kirjath Jearim came and took the ark of the Lord,
        and brought it into the house of Abinadab on the hill, and consecrated Eleazar
        his son to keep the ark of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So it was that the ark remained in Kirjath Jearim a long time; it
        was there twenty years. And all the house of Israel lamented after the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Samuel spoke to all the house of Israel, saying, \u201CIf you
        return to the Lord with all your hearts, then  put away the foreign gods
        and the Ashtoreths from among you, and prepare your hearts for the Lord,
        and serve Him only; and He will deliver you from the hand of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So the children of Israel put away the Baals and the Ashtoreths, and
        served the Lord only.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Samuel said, \u201CGather all Israel to Mizpah, and I will pray
        to the Lord for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they gathered together at Mizpah, drew water, and poured it out
        before the Lord. And they fasted that day, and said there, \u201CWe have
        sinned against the Lord.\u201D And Samuel judged the children of Israel at
        Mizpah."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when the Philistines heard that the children of Israel had gathered
        together at Mizpah, the lords of the Philistines went up against Israel.
        And when the children of Israel heard of  it, they were afraid of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the children of Israel said to Samuel, \u201CDo not cease to cry
        out to the Lord our God for us, that He may save us from the hand of the
        Philistines.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Samuel took a suckling lamb and offered it  as a whole burnt
        offering to the Lord. Then Samuel cried out to the Lord for Israel, and the
        Lord answered him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now as Samuel was offering up the burnt offering, the Philistines
        drew near to battle against Israel. But the Lord thundered with a loud thunder
        upon the Philistines that day, and so confused them that they were overcome
        before Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the men of Israel went out of Mizpah and pursued the Philistines,
        and drove them back as far as below Beth Car. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Samuel took a stone and set it up between Mizpah and Shen, and
        called its name Ebenezer, saying, \u201CThus far the Lord has helped us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the Philistines were subdued, and they did not come anymore into
        the territory of Israel. And the hand of the Lord was against the Philistines
        all the days of Samuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Then the cities which the Philistines had taken from Israel were restored
        to Israel, from Ekron to Gath; and Israel recovered its territory from the
        hands of the Philistines. Also there was peace between Israel and the Amorites.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Samuel judged Israel all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He went from year to year on a circuit to Bethel, Gilgal, and Mizpah,
        and judged Israel in all those places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But he always returned to Ramah, for his home was there. There he
        judged Israel, and there he built an altar to the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Demands a King'
      title: Israel Demands a King
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass when Samuel was old that he made his sons judges
        over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The name of his firstborn was Joel, and the name of his second, Abijah;
        they  were judges in Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: But his sons did not walk in his ways; they turned aside after dishonest
        gain, took bribes, and perverted justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then all the elders of Israel gathered together and came to Samuel
        at Ramah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and said to him, \u201CLook, you are old, and your sons do not walk
        in your ways. Now make us a king to judge us like all the nations.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But the thing displeased Samuel when they said, \u201CGive us a king
        to judge us.\u201D So Samuel prayed to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the Lord said to Samuel, \u201CHeed the voice of the people in
        all that they say to you; for they have not rejected you, but they have rejected
        Me, that I should not reign over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "According to all the works which they have done since the day that
        I brought them up out of Egypt, even to this day\u2014with which they have
        forsaken Me and served other gods\u2014so they are doing to you also. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now therefore, heed their voice. However, you shall solemnly forewarn
        them, and show them the behavior of the king who will reign over them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Samuel told all the words of the Lord to the people who asked
        him for a king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he said, \u201CThis will be the behavior of the king who will
        reign over you: He will take your sons and appoint them for his own chariots
        and to  be his horsemen, and some will run before his chariots. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He will appoint captains over his thousands and captains over his
        fifties, will  set  some to plow his ground and reap his harvest, and some
        to make his weapons of war and equipment for his chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will take your daughters to  be perfumers, cooks, and bakers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he will take the best of your fields, your vineyards, and your
        olive groves, and give them to his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He will take a tenth of your grain and your vintage, and give it
        to his officers and servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And he will take your male servants, your female servants, your finest
        young men, and your donkeys, and put them to his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He will take a tenth of your sheep. And you will be his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And you will cry out in that day because of your king whom you have
        chosen for yourselves, and the Lord  will not hear you in that day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Nevertheless the people refused to obey the voice of Samuel; and
        they said, \u201CNo, but we will have a king over us, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "that we also may be like all the nations, and that our king may judge
        us and go out before us and fight our battles.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Samuel heard all the words of the people, and he repeated them
        in the hearing of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So the Lord said to Samuel, \u201CHeed their voice, and make them
        a king.\u201DAnd Samuel said to the men of Israel, \u201CEvery man go to
        his city.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Chosen to Be King'
      title: Saul Chosen to Be King
      number: 1
      content: 'There was a man of Benjamin whose name was  Kish the son of Abiel,
        the son of Zeror, the son of Bechorath, the son of Aphiah, a Benjamite, a
        mighty man of power. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And he had a choice and handsome son whose name was Saul. There  was
        not a more handsome person than he among the children of Israel. From his
        shoulders upward he  was taller than any of the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now the donkeys of Kish, Saul\u2019s father, were lost. And Kish
        said to his son Saul, \u201CPlease take one of the servants with you, and
        arise, go and look for the donkeys.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So he passed through the mountains of Ephraim and through the land
        of Shalisha, but they did not find them. Then they passed through the land
        of Shaalim, and they  were not there. Then he passed through the land of
        the Benjamites, but they did not find them.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When they had come to the land of Zuph, Saul said to his servant
        who was with him, \u201CCome, let us return, lest my father cease caring
        about the donkeys and become worried about us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CLook now, there  is in this city a man
        of God, and he  is an honorable man; all that he says surely comes to pass.
        So let us go there; perhaps he can show us the way that we should go.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Saul said to his servant, \u201CBut look, if we go, what shall
        we bring the man? For the bread in our vessels is all gone, and there  is
        no present to bring to the man of God. What do we have?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the servant answered Saul again and said, \u201CLook, I have
        here at hand one-fourth of a shekel of silver. I will give that to the man
        of God, to tell us our way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "(Formerly in Israel, when a man went to inquire of God, he spoke
        thus: \u201CCome, let us go to the seer\u201D; for he  who  is now called
        a prophet was formerly called a seer.)"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Saul said to his servant, \u201CWell said; come, let us go.\u201D
        So they went to the city where the man of God was."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As they went up the hill to the city, they met some young women going
        out to draw water, and said to them, \u201CIs the seer here?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they answered them and said, \u201CYes, there he is, just ahead
        of you. Hurry now; for today he came to this city, because there is a sacrifice
        of the people today on the high place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As soon as you come into the city, you will surely find him before
        he goes up to the high place to eat. For the people will not eat until he
        comes, because he must bless the sacrifice; afterward those who are invited
        will eat. Now therefore, go up, for about this time you will find him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So they went up to the city. As they were coming into the city, there
        was Samuel, coming out toward them on his way up to the high place.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the Lord had told Samuel in his ear the day before Saul came,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CTomorrow about this time I will send you a man from the land
        of Benjamin, and you shall anoint him commander over My people Israel, that
        he may save My people from the hand of the Philistines; for I have looked
        upon My people, because their cry has come to Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So when Samuel saw Saul, the Lord said to him, \u201CThere he is,
        the man of whom I spoke to you. This one shall reign over My people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Saul drew near to Samuel in the gate, and said, \u201CPlease
        tell me, where is the seer\u2019s house?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Samuel answered Saul and said, \u201CI am the seer. Go up before
        me to the high place, for you shall eat with me today; and tomorrow I will
        let you go and will tell you all that is in your heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But as for your donkeys that were lost three days ago, do not be
        anxious about them, for they have been found. And on whom is all the desire
        of Israel? Is  it not on you and on all your father\u2019s house?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Saul answered and said, \u201CAm I not a Benjamite, of the smallest
        of the tribes of Israel, and my family the least of all the families of the
        tribe of Benjamin? Why then do you speak like this to me?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now Samuel took Saul and his servant and brought them into the hall,
        and had them sit in the place of honor among those who were invited; there
        were about thirty persons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Samuel said to the cook, \u201CBring the portion which I gave
        you, of which I said to you, \u2018Set it apart.\u2019 \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the cook took up the thigh with its upper part and set it before
        Saul. And Samuel said, \u201CHere it is, what was kept back. It was set apart
        for you. Eat; for until this time it has been kept for you, since I said
        I invited the people.\u201D So Saul ate with Samuel that day."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When they had come down from the high place into the city, Samuel
        spoke with Saul on the top of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Saul Anointed King'
      title: Saul Anointed King
      number: 26
      content: "They arose early; and it was about the dawning of the day that Samuel
        called to Saul on the top of the house, saying, \u201CGet up, that I may
        send you on your way.\u201D And Saul arose, and both of them went outside,
        he and Samuel."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "As they were going down to the outskirts of the city, Samuel said
        to Saul, \u201CTell the servant to go on ahead of us.\u201D And he went on.
        \u201CBut you stand here awhile, that I may announce to you the word of God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Then Samuel took a flask of oil and poured it on his head, and kissed
        him and said: \u201CIs  it not because the Lord has anointed you commander
        over His inheritance? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When you have departed from me today, you will find two men by Rachel\u2019s
        tomb in the territory of Benjamin at Zelzah; and they will say to you, \u2018The
        donkeys which you went to look for have been found. And now your father has
        ceased caring about the donkeys and is worrying about you, saying, \u201CWhat
        shall I do about my son?\u201D \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then you shall go on forward from there and come to the terebinth
        tree of Tabor. There three men going up to God at Bethel will meet you, one
        carrying three young goats, another carrying three loaves of bread, and another
        carrying a skin of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they will greet you and give you two loaves of bread, which you
        shall receive from their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'After that you shall come to the hill of God where the Philistine
        garrison is. And it will happen, when you have come there to the city, that
        you will meet a group of prophets coming down from the high place with a
        stringed instrument, a tambourine, a flute, and a harp before them; and they
        will be prophesying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Spirit of the Lord will come upon you, and you will prophesy
        with them and be turned into another man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And let it be, when these signs come to you, that you do as the occasion
        demands; for God is with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You shall go down before me to Gilgal; and surely I will come down
        to you to offer burnt offerings and make sacrifices of peace offerings. Seven
        days you shall wait, till I come to you and show you what you should do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So it was, when he had turned his back to go from Samuel, that God
        gave him another heart; and all those signs came to pass that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they came there to the hill, there was a group of prophets to
        meet him; then the Spirit of God came upon him, and he prophesied among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And it happened, when all who knew him formerly saw that he indeed
        prophesied among the prophets, that the people said to one another, \u201CWhat
        is this that has come upon the son of Kish? Is Saul also among the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then a man from there answered and said, \u201CBut who is their father?\u201D
        Therefore it became a proverb: \u201CIs Saul also among the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And when he had finished prophesying, he went to the high place.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Saul\u2019s uncle said to him and his servant, \u201CWhere did
        you go?\u201DSo he said, \u201CTo look for the donkeys. When we saw that
        they  were nowhere to  be  found, we went to Samuel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Saul\u2019s uncle said, \u201CTell me, please, what Samuel said
        to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Saul Proclaimed King'
      title: Saul Proclaimed King
      number: 16
      content: "So Saul said to his uncle, \u201CHe told us plainly that the donkeys
        had been found.\u201D But about the matter of the kingdom, he did not tell
        him what Samuel had said."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Samuel called the people together to the Lord  at Mizpah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and said to the children of Israel, \u201CThus says the Lord God
        of Israel: \u2018I brought up Israel out of Egypt, and delivered you from
        the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand of all kingdoms and from those
        who oppressed you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But you have today rejected your God, who Himself saved you from
        all your adversities and your tribulations; and you have said to Him, \u2018No,
        set a king over us!\u2019 Now therefore, present yourselves before the Lord
        by your tribes and by your clans.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when Samuel had caused all the tribes of Israel to come near,
        the tribe of Benjamin was chosen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When he had caused the tribe of Benjamin to come near by their families,
        the family of Matri was chosen. And Saul the son of Kish was chosen. But
        when they sought him, he could not be found. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore they inquired of the Lord further, \u201CHas the man come
        here yet?\u201DAnd the Lord answered, \u201CThere he is, hidden among the
        equipment.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So they ran and brought him from there; and when he stood among the
        people, he was taller than any of the people from his shoulders upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Samuel said to all the people, \u201CDo you see him whom the
        Lord has chosen, that there  is no one like him among all the people?\u201DSo
        all the people shouted and said, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Samuel explained to the people the behavior of royalty, and
        wrote it in a book and laid it up before the Lord. And Samuel sent all the
        people away, every man to his house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Saul also went home to Gibeah; and valiant men went with him,
        whose hearts God had touched. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But some rebels said, \u201CHow can this man save us?\u201D So they
        despised him, and brought him no presents. But he held his peace."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Saves Jabesh Gilead'
      title: Saul Saves Jabesh Gilead
      number: 1
      content: "Then Nahash the Ammonite came up and encamped against Jabesh Gilead;
        and all the men of Jabesh said to Nahash, \u201CMake a covenant with us,
        and we will serve you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Nahash the Ammonite answered them, \u201COn this condition I
        will make a  covenant with you, that I may put out all your right eyes, and
        bring reproach on all Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the elders of Jabesh said to him, \u201CHold off for seven days,
        that we may send messengers to all the territory of Israel. And then, if
        there  is no one to save us, we will come out to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the messengers came to Gibeah of Saul and told the news in the
        hearing of the people. And all the people lifted up their voices and wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now there was Saul, coming behind the herd from the field; and Saul
        said, \u201CWhat troubles the people, that they weep?\u201D And they told
        him the words of the men of Jabesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Spirit of God came upon Saul when he heard this news, and
        his anger was greatly aroused. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So he took a yoke of oxen and cut them in pieces, and sent them throughout
        all the territory of Israel by the hands of messengers, saying, \u201CWhoever
        does not go out with Saul and Samuel to battle, so it shall be done to his
        oxen.\u201DAnd the fear of the Lord fell on the people, and they came out
        with one consent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When he numbered them in Bezek, the children of Israel were three
        hundred thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And they said to the messengers who came, \u201CThus you shall say
        to the men of Jabesh Gilead: \u2018Tomorrow, by the  time the sun is hot,
        you shall have help.\u2019 \u201D Then the messengers came and reported it
        to the men of Jabesh, and they were glad. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore the men of Jabesh said, \u201CTomorrow we will come out
        to you, and you may do with us whatever seems good to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So it was, on the next day, that Saul put the people in three companies;
        and they came into the midst of the camp in the morning watch, and killed
        Ammonites until the heat of the day. And it happened that those who survived
        were scattered, so that no two of them were left together.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the people said to Samuel, \u201CWho is he who said, \u2018Shall
        Saul reign over us?\u2019 Bring the men, that we may put them to death.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Saul said, \u201CNot a man shall be put to death this day, for
        today the Lord has accomplished salvation in Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Samuel said to the people, \u201CCome, let us go to Gilgal and
        renew the kingdom there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So all the people went to Gilgal, and there they made Saul king before
        the Lord in Gilgal. There they made sacrifices of peace offerings before
        the Lord, and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samuel\u2019s Address at Saul\u2019s Coronation"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s Address at Saul\u2019s Coronation"
      number: 1
      content: "Now Samuel said to all Israel: \u201CIndeed I have heeded your voice
        in all that you said to me, and have made a king over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And now here is the king, walking before you; and I am old and grayheaded,
        and look, my sons are with you. I have walked before you from my childhood
        to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Here I am. Witness against me before the Lord and before His anointed:
        Whose ox have I taken, or whose donkey have I taken, or whom have I cheated?
        Whom have I oppressed, or from whose hand have I received any  bribe with
        which to blind my eyes? I will restore it to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they said, \u201CYou have not cheated us or oppressed us, nor
        have you taken anything from any man\u2019s hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CThe Lord  is witness against you, and
        His anointed is witness this day, that you have not found anything in my
        hand.\u201DAnd they answered, \u201CHe  is witness.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Samuel said to the people, \u201CIt  is the Lord who raised
        up Moses and Aaron, and who brought your fathers up from the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now therefore, stand still, that I may reason with you before the
        Lord concerning all the righteous acts of the Lord which He did to you and
        your fathers: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When Jacob had gone into Egypt, and your fathers cried out to the
        Lord, then the Lord  sent Moses and Aaron, who brought your fathers out of
        Egypt and made them dwell in this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when they forgot the Lord their God, He sold them into the hand
        of Sisera, commander of the army of Hazor, into the hand of the Philistines,
        and into the hand of the king of Moab; and they fought against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then they cried out to the Lord, and said, \u2018We have sinned,
        because we have forsaken the Lord  and served the Baals and Ashtoreths; but
        now deliver us from the hand of our enemies, and we will serve You.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the Lord sent Jerubbaal, Bedan, Jephthah, and Samuel, and delivered
        you out of the hand of your enemies on every side; and you dwelt in safety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And when you saw that Nahash king of the Ammonites came against you,
        you said to me, \u2018No, but a king shall reign over us,\u2019 when the
        Lord your God was your king."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, here is the king whom you have chosen and whom
        you have desired. And take note, the Lord has set a king over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If you fear the Lord and serve Him and obey His voice, and do not
        rebel against the commandment of the Lord, then both you and the king who
        reigns over you will continue following the Lord your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: However, if you do not obey the voice of the Lord, but rebel against
        the commandment of the Lord, then the hand of the Lord will be against you,
        as it  was against your fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, stand and see this great thing which the Lord
        will do before your eyes: "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Is today not the wheat harvest? I will call to the Lord, and He will
        send thunder and rain, that you may perceive and see that your wickedness
        is great, which you have done in the sight of the Lord, in asking a king
        for yourselves.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: So Samuel called to the Lord, and the Lord sent thunder and rain that
        day; and all the people greatly feared the Lord and Samuel.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And all the people said to Samuel, \u201CPray for your servants to
        the Lord your God, that we may not die; for we have added to all our sins
        the evil of asking a king for ourselves.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Samuel said to the people, \u201CDo not fear. You have done
        all this wickedness; yet do not turn aside from following the Lord, but serve
        the Lord with all your heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And do not turn aside; for then  you  would  go after empty things
        which cannot profit or deliver, for they are nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "For the Lord will not forsake His people, for His great name\u2019s
        sake, because it has pleased the Lord to make you His people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Moreover, as for me, far be it from me that I should sin against
        the Lord  in ceasing to pray for you; but I will teach you the good and the
        right way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Only fear the Lord, and serve Him in truth with all your heart; for
        consider what great things He has done for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But if you still do wickedly, you shall be swept away, both you and
        your king.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Saul\u2019s Unlawful Sacrifice"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Unlawful Sacrifice"
      number: 1
      content: 'Saul reigned one year; and when he had reigned two years over Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Saul chose for himself three thousand men of Israel. Two thousand
        were with Saul in Michmash and in the mountains of Bethel, and a thousand
        were with Jonathan in Gibeah of Benjamin. The rest of the people he sent
        away, every man to his tent.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And Jonathan attacked the garrison of the Philistines that was in
        Geba, and the Philistines heard of  it. Then Saul blew the trumpet throughout
        all the land, saying, \u201CLet the Hebrews hear!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Now all Israel heard it said that Saul had attacked a garrison of
        the Philistines, and that Israel had also become an abomination to the Philistines.
        And the people were called together to Saul at Gilgal.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the Philistines gathered together to fight with Israel, thirty
        thousand chariots and six thousand horsemen, and people as the sand which
        is on the seashore in multitude. And they came up and encamped in Michmash,
        to the east of Beth Aven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the men of Israel saw that they were in danger (for the people
        were distressed), then the people hid in caves, in thickets, in rocks, in
        holes, and in pits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And some  of the Hebrews crossed over the Jordan to the land of Gad
        and Gilead.As for Saul, he was still in Gilgal, and all the people followed
        him trembling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he waited seven days, according to the time set by Samuel. But
        Samuel did not come to Gilgal; and the people were scattered from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Saul said, \u201CBring a burnt offering and peace offerings here
        to me.\u201D And he offered the burnt offering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Now it happened, as soon as he had finished presenting the burnt offering,
        that Samuel came; and Saul went out to meet him, that he might greet him.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Samuel said, \u201CWhat have you done?\u201DSaul said, \u201CWhen
        I saw that the people were scattered from me, and that you did not come within
        the days appointed, and that the Philistines gathered together at Michmash, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "then I said, \u2018The Philistines will now come down on me at Gilgal,
        and I have not made supplication to the Lord.\u2019 Therefore I felt compelled,
        and offered a burnt offering.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Samuel said to Saul, \u201CYou have done foolishly. You have
        not kept the commandment of the Lord your God, which He commanded you. For
        now the Lord would have established your kingdom over Israel forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now your kingdom shall not continue. The Lord has sought for
        Himself a man after His own heart, and the Lord has commanded him to  be
        commander over His people, because you have not kept what the Lord commanded
        you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: No Weapons for the Army'
      title: No Weapons for the Army
      number: 15
      content: Then Samuel arose and went up from Gilgal to Gibeah of Benjamin. And
        Saul numbered the people present with him, about six hundred men.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Saul, Jonathan his son, and the people present with them remained
        in Gibeah of Benjamin. But the Philistines encamped in Michmash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then raiders came out of the camp of the Philistines in three companies.
        One company turned onto the road to Ophrah, to the land of Shual, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: another company turned to the road to  Beth Horon, and another company
        turned to the road of the border that overlooks the Valley of Zeboim toward
        the wilderness.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now there was no blacksmith to be found throughout all the land of
        Israel, for the Philistines said, \u201CLest the Hebrews make swords or spears.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But all the Israelites would go down to the Philistines to sharpen
        each man\u2019s plowshare, his mattock, his ax, and his sickle; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and the charge for a sharpening was a pim for the plowshares, the
        mattocks, the forks, and the axes, and to set the points of the goads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So it came about, on the day of battle, that there was neither sword
        nor spear found in the hand of any of the people who were with Saul and Jonathan.
        But they were found with Saul and Jonathan his son.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And the garrison of the Philistines went out to the pass of Michmash.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jonathan Defeats the Philistines'
      title: Jonathan Defeats the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: "Now it happened one day that Jonathan the son of Saul said to the
        young man who bore his armor, \u201CCome, let us go over to the Philistines\u2019
        garrison that is on the other side.\u201D But he did not tell his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Saul was sitting in the outskirts of Gibeah under a pomegranate
        tree which is in Migron. The people who were with him were about six hundred
        men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Ahijah the son of Ahitub, Ichabod\u2019s brother, the son of Phinehas,
        the son of Eli, the Lord\u2019s priest in Shiloh, was wearing an ephod. But
        the people did not know that Jonathan had gone."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Between the passes, by which Jonathan sought to go over to the Philistines\u2019
        garrison, there  was a sharp rock on one side and a sharp rock on the other
        side. And the name of one was Bozez, and the name of the other Seneh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The front of one faced northward opposite Michmash, and the other
        southward opposite Gibeah.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Jonathan said to the young man who bore his armor, \u201CCome,
        let us go over to the garrison of these uncircumcised; it may be that the
        Lord will work for us. For nothing restrains the Lord  from saving by many
        or by few.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So his armorbearer said to him, \u201CDo all that is in your heart.
        Go then; here I am with you, according to your heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Jonathan said, \u201CVery well, let us cross over to these men,
        and we will show ourselves to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If they say thus to us, \u2018Wait until we come to you,\u2019 then
        we will stand still in our place and not go up to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But if they say thus, \u2018Come up to us,\u2019 then we will go
        up. For the Lord has delivered them into our hand, and this will  be a sign
        to us.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So both of them showed themselves to the garrison of the Philistines.
        And the Philistines said, \u201CLook, the Hebrews are coming out of the holes
        where they have hidden.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the men of the garrison called to Jonathan and his armorbearer,
        and said, \u201CCome up to us, and we will show you something.\u201DJonathan
        said to his armorbearer, \u201CCome up after me, for the Lord has delivered
        them into the hand of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Jonathan climbed up on his hands and knees with his armorbearer
        after him; and they fell before Jonathan. And as he came after him, his armorbearer
        killed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: That first slaughter which Jonathan and his armorbearer made was about
        twenty men within about half an acre of land.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And there was trembling in the camp, in the field, and among all
        the people. The garrison and the raiders also trembled; and the earth quaked,
        so that it was a very great trembling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now the watchmen of Saul in Gibeah of Benjamin looked, and there
        was the multitude, melting away; and they went here and there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to the people who were with him, \u201CNow call the
        roll and see who has gone from us.\u201D And when they had called the roll,
        surprisingly, Jonathan and his armorbearer were not there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Saul said to Ahijah, \u201CBring the ark of God here\u201D (for
        at that time the ark of God was with the children of Israel). "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now it happened, while Saul talked to the priest, that the noise
        which was in the camp of the Philistines continued to increase; so Saul said
        to the priest, \u201CWithdraw your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Saul and all the people who were with him assembled, and they
        went to the battle; and indeed every man\u2019s sword was against his neighbor,
        and  there  was very great confusion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Moreover the Hebrews who were with the Philistines before that time,
        who went up with them into the camp from  the surrounding country, they also
        joined the Israelites who were with Saul and Jonathan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Likewise all the men of Israel who had hidden in the mountains of
        Ephraim, when they heard that the Philistines fled, they also followed hard
        after them in the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Saul\u2019s Rash Oath"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Rash Oath"
      number: 23
      content: So the Lord saved Israel that day, and the battle shifted to Beth
        Aven.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the men of Israel were distressed that day, for Saul had placed
        the people under oath, saying, \u201CCursed is the man who eats any food
        until evening, before I have taken vengeance on my enemies.\u201D So none
        of the people tasted food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now all the  people of the land came to a forest; and there was honey
        on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And when the people had come into the woods, there was the honey,
        dripping; but no one put his hand to his mouth, for the people feared the
        oath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But Jonathan had not heard his father charge the people with the
        oath; therefore he stretched out the end of the rod that was in his hand
        and dipped it in a honeycomb, and put his hand to his mouth; and his countenance
        brightened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then one of the people said, \u201CYour father strictly charged the
        people with an oath, saying, \u2018Cursed is the man who eats food this day.\u2019
        \u201D And the people were faint."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But Jonathan said, \u201CMy father has troubled the land. Look now,
        how my countenance has brightened because I tasted a little of this honey. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "How much better if the people had eaten freely today of the spoil
        of their enemies which they found! For now would there not have been a much
        greater slaughter among the Philistines?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now they had driven back the Philistines that day from Michmash to
        Aijalon. So the people were very faint. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the people rushed on the spoil, and took sheep, oxen, and calves,
        and slaughtered them on the ground; and the people ate them  with the blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then they told Saul, saying, \u201CLook, the people are sinning against
        the Lord by eating with the blood!\u201DSo he said, \u201CYou have dealt
        treacherously; roll a large stone to me this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CDisperse yourselves among the people, and say
        to them, \u2018Bring me here every man\u2019s ox and every man\u2019s sheep,
        slaughter them here, and eat; and do not sin against the Lord by eating with
        the blood.\u2019 \u201D So every one of the people brought his ox with him
        that night, and slaughtered it there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Then Saul built an altar to the Lord. This was the first altar that
        he built to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Now Saul said, \u201CLet us go down after the Philistines by night,
        and plunder them until the morning light; and let us not leave a man of them.\u201DAnd
        they said, \u201CDo whatever seems good to you.\u201DThen the priest said,
        \u201CLet us draw near to God here.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "So Saul asked counsel of God, \u201CShall I go down after the Philistines?
        Will You deliver them into the hand of Israel?\u201D But He did not answer
        him that day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CCome over here, all you chiefs of the people,
        and know and see what this sin was today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "For as the Lord lives, who saves Israel, though it be in Jonathan
        my son, he shall surely die.\u201D But not a man among all the people answered
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he said to all Israel, \u201CYou be on one side, and my son
        Jonathan and I will be on the other side.\u201DAnd the people said to Saul,
        \u201CDo what seems good to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Therefore Saul said to the Lord God of Israel, \u201CGive a perfect
        lot.\u201D So Saul and Jonathan were taken, but the people escaped. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CCast lots between my son Jonathan and me.\u201D
        So Jonathan was taken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Then Saul said to Jonathan, \u201CTell me what you have done.\u201DAnd
        Jonathan told him, and said, \u201CI only tasted a little honey with the
        end of the rod that was in my hand. So now I must die!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Saul answered, \u201CGod do so and more also; for you shall surely
        die, Jonathan.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "But the people said to Saul, \u201CShall Jonathan die, who has accomplished
        this great deliverance in Israel? Certainly not! As the Lord lives, not one
        hair of his head shall fall to the ground, for he has worked with God this
        day.\u201D So the people rescued Jonathan, and he did not die."
      comments: []
    - name: "46: Saul\u2019s Continuing Wars"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Continuing Wars"
      number: 46
      content: Then Saul returned from pursuing the Philistines, and the Philistines
        went to their own place.
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'So Saul established his sovereignty over Israel, and fought against
        all his enemies on every side, against Moab, against the people of Ammon,
        against Edom, against the kings of Zobah, and against the Philistines. Wherever
        he turned, he harassed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: And he gathered an army and attacked the Amalekites, and delivered
        Israel from the hands of those who plundered them.
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'The sons of Saul were Jonathan, Jishui, and Malchishua. And the names
        of his two daughters were  these: the name of the firstborn Merab, and the
        name of the younger Michal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "The name of Saul\u2019s wife was Ahinoam the daughter of Ahimaaz.
        And the name of the commander of his army was Abner the son of Ner, Saul\u2019s
        uncle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: Kish was the father of Saul, and Ner the father of Abner was the son
        of Abiel.
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: Now there was fierce war with the Philistines all the days of Saul.
        And when Saul saw any strong man or any valiant man, he took him for himself.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Spares King Agag'
      title: Saul Spares King Agag
      number: 1
      content: "Samuel also said to Saul, \u201CThe Lord sent me to anoint you king
        over His people, over Israel. Now therefore, heed the voice of the words
        of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts: \u2018I will punish Amalek for what
        he did to Israel, how he ambushed him on the way when he came up from Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now go and attack Amalek, and utterly destroy all that they have,
        and do not spare them. But kill both man and woman, infant and nursing child,
        ox and sheep, camel and donkey.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Saul gathered the people together and numbered them in Telaim,
        two hundred thousand foot soldiers and ten thousand men of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And Saul came to a city of Amalek, and lay in wait in the valley.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Saul said to the Kenites, \u201CGo, depart, get down from among
        the Amalekites, lest I destroy you with them. For you showed kindness to
        all the children of Israel when they came up out of Egypt.\u201D So the Kenites
        departed from among the Amalekites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Saul attacked the Amalekites, from Havilah all the way to Shur,
        which is east of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He also took Agag king of the Amalekites alive, and utterly destroyed
        all the people with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Saul Rejected as King'
      title: Saul Rejected as King
      number: 9
      content: But Saul and the people spared Agag and the best of the sheep, the
        oxen, the fatlings, the lambs, and all that  was good, and were unwilling
        to utterly destroy them. But everything despised and worthless, that they
        utterly destroyed.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the word of the Lord came to Samuel, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI greatly regret that I have set up Saul as king, for he has
        turned back from following Me, and has not performed My commandments.\u201D
        And it grieved Samuel, and he cried out to the Lord all night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So when Samuel rose early in the morning to meet Saul, it was told
        Samuel, saying, \u201CSaul went to Carmel, and indeed, he set up a monument
        for himself; and he has gone on around, passed by, and gone down to Gilgal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Samuel went to Saul, and Saul said to him, \u201CBlessed are
        you of the Lord! I have performed the commandment of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Samuel said, \u201CWhat then is this bleating of the sheep in
        my ears, and the lowing of the oxen which I hear?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CThey have brought them from the Amalekites;
        for the people spared the best of the sheep and the oxen, to sacrifice to
        the Lord your God; and the rest we have utterly destroyed.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CBe quiet! And I will tell you what
        the Lord said to me last night.\u201DAnd he said to him, \u201CSpeak on.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Samuel said, \u201CWhen you were little in your own eyes, were
        you not head of the tribes of Israel? And did not the Lord anoint you king
        over Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now the Lord sent you on a mission, and said, \u2018Go, and utterly
        destroy the sinners, the Amalekites, and fight against them until they are
        consumed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why then did you not obey the voice of the Lord? Why did you swoop
        down on the spoil, and do evil in the sight of the Lord?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Saul said to Samuel, \u201CBut I have obeyed the voice of the
        Lord, and gone on the mission on which the Lord sent me, and brought back
        Agag king of Amalek; I have utterly destroyed the Amalekites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But the people took of the plunder, sheep and oxen, the best of the
        things which should have been utterly destroyed, to sacrifice to the Lord
        your God in Gilgal.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So Samuel said:\u201CHas the Lord  as  great delight in burnt offerings
        and sacrifices,As in obeying the voice of the Lord?Behold, to obey is better
        than sacrifice,And to heed than the fat of rams."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For rebellion is  as the sin of witchcraft,And stubbornness is  as
        iniquity and idolatry.Because you have rejected the word of the Lord,He also
        has rejected you from being king.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Saul said to Samuel, \u201CI have sinned, for I have transgressed
        the commandment of the Lord and your words, because I feared the people and
        obeyed their voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now therefore, please pardon my sin, and return with me, that I may
        worship the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Samuel said to Saul, \u201CI will not return with you, for you
        have rejected the word of the Lord, and the Lord has rejected you from being
        king over Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And as Samuel turned around to go away, Saul seized the edge of his
        robe, and it tore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Samuel said to him, \u201CThe Lord has torn the kingdom of Israel
        from you today, and has given it to a neighbor of yours, who  is better than
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And also the Strength of Israel will not lie nor relent. For He is
        not a man, that He should relent.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI have sinned; yet  honor me now, please, before
        the elders of my people and before Israel, and return with me, that I may
        worship the Lord your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: So Samuel turned back after Saul, and Saul worshiped the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Samuel said, \u201CBring Agag king of the Amalekites here to
        me.\u201D So Agag came to him cautiously.And Agag said, \u201CSurely the
        bitterness of death is past.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But Samuel said, \u201CAs your sword has made women childless, so
        shall your mother be childless among women.\u201D And Samuel hacked Agag
        in pieces before the Lord in Gilgal."
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Samuel went to Ramah, and Saul went up to his house at Gibeah
        of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: And Samuel went no more to see Saul until the day of his death. Nevertheless
        Samuel mourned for Saul, and the Lord regretted that He had made Saul king
        over Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Anointed King'
      title: David Anointed King
      number: 1
      content: "Now the Lord said to Samuel, \u201CHow long will you mourn for Saul,
        seeing I have rejected him from reigning over Israel? Fill your horn with
        oil, and go; I am sending you to Jesse the Bethlehemite. For I have provided
        Myself a king among his sons.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Samuel said, \u201CHow can I go? If Saul hears it, he will kill
        me.\u201DBut the Lord said, \u201CTake a heifer with you, and say, \u2018I
        have come to sacrifice to the Lord.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then invite Jesse to the sacrifice, and I will show you what you
        shall do; you shall anoint for Me the one I name to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Samuel did what the Lord said, and went to Bethlehem. And the
        elders of the town trembled at his coming, and said, \u201CDo you come peaceably?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he said, \u201CPeaceably; I have come to sacrifice to the Lord.
        Sanctify yourselves, and come with me to the sacrifice.\u201D Then he consecrated
        Jesse and his sons, and invited them to the sacrifice."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So it was, when they came, that he looked at Eliab and said, \u201CSurely
        the Lord\u2019s anointed is before Him!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the Lord said to Samuel, \u201CDo not look at his appearance
        or at his physical stature, because I have refused him. For the  Lord  does
        not see as man sees; for man looks at the outward appearance, but the Lord
        looks at the heart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Jesse called Abinadab, and made him pass before Samuel. And he
        said, \u201CNeither has the Lord chosen this one.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Jesse made Shammah pass by. And he said, \u201CNeither has the
        Lord chosen this one.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Thus Jesse made seven of his sons pass before Samuel. And Samuel
        said to Jesse, \u201CThe Lord has not chosen these.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Samuel said to Jesse, \u201CAre all the young men here?\u201D
        Then he said, \u201CThere remains yet the youngest, and there he is, keeping
        the sheep.\u201DAnd Samuel said to Jesse, \u201CSend and bring him. For we
        will not sit down till he comes here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So he sent and brought him in. Now he was  ruddy, with bright eyes,
        and good-looking. And the Lord said, \u201CArise, anoint him; for this is
        the one!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: A Distressing Spirit Troubles Saul'
      title: A Distressing Spirit Troubles Saul
      number: 13
      content: Then Samuel took the horn of oil and anointed him in the midst of
        his brothers; and the Spirit of the Lord came upon David from that day forward.
        So Samuel arose and went to Ramah.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the Spirit of the Lord departed from Saul, and a distressing
        spirit from the Lord troubled him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Saul\u2019s servants said to him, \u201CSurely, a distressing
        spirit from God is troubling you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Let our master now command your servants, who  are before you, to
        seek out a man who  is a skillful player on the harp. And it shall be that
        he will play it with his hand when the distressing spirit from God is upon
        you, and you shall be well.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Saul said to his servants, \u201CProvide me now a man who can
        play well, and bring him to me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then one of the servants answered and said, \u201CLook, I have seen
        a son of Jesse the Bethlehemite, who  is skillful in playing, a mighty man
        of valor, a man of war, prudent in speech, and a handsome person; and the
        Lord  is with him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore Saul sent messengers to Jesse, and said, \u201CSend me
        your son David, who is with the sheep.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Jesse took a donkey loaded  with bread, a skin of wine, and a
        young goat, and sent them by his son David to Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So David came to Saul and stood before him. And he loved him greatly,
        and he became his armorbearer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Saul sent to Jesse, saying, \u201CPlease let David stand before
        me, for he has found favor in my sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And so it was, whenever the spirit from God was upon Saul, that David
        would take a harp and play it with his hand. Then Saul would become refreshed
        and well, and the distressing spirit would depart from him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David and Goliath'
      title: David and Goliath
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Philistines gathered their armies together to battle, and
        were gathered at Sochoh, which belongs to Judah; they encamped between Sochoh
        and Azekah, in Ephes Dammim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Saul and the men of Israel were gathered together, and they encamped
        in the Valley of Elah, and drew up in battle array against the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The Philistines stood on a mountain on one side, and Israel stood
        on a mountain on the other side, with a valley between them.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And a champion went out from the camp of the Philistines, named Goliath,
        from Gath, whose height was six cubits and a span. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He  had a bronze helmet on his head, and he was armed with a coat
        of mail, and the weight of the coat was five thousand shekels of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he  had bronze armor on his legs and a bronze javelin between
        his shoulders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now the staff of his spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam, and his
        iron spearhead weighed six hundred shekels; and a shield-bearer went before
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he stood and cried out to the armies of Israel, and said to
        them, \u201CWhy have you come out to line up for battle? Am I not a Philistine,
        and you the servants of Saul? Choose a man for yourselves, and let him come
        down to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If he is able to fight with me and kill me, then we will be your
        servants. But if I prevail against him and kill him, then you shall be our
        servants and serve us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the Philistine said, \u201CI defy the armies of Israel this day;
        give me a man, that we may fight together.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: When Saul and all Israel heard these words of the Philistine, they
        were dismayed and greatly afraid.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now David was  the son of that Ephrathite of Bethlehem Judah, whose
        name was Jesse, and who had eight sons. And the man was old, advanced in 
        years, in the days of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The three oldest sons of Jesse had gone to follow Saul to the battle.
        The names of his three sons who went to the battle were Eliab the firstborn,
        next to him Abinadab, and the third Shammah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David was the youngest. And the three oldest followed Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But David occasionally went and returned from Saul to feed his father\u2019s
        sheep at Bethlehem."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And the Philistine drew near and presented himself forty days, morning
        and evening.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jesse said to his son David, \u201CTake now for your brothers
        an ephah of this dried grain and these ten loaves, and run to your brothers
        at the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And carry these ten cheeses to the captain of their thousand, and
        see how your brothers fare, and bring back news of them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Now Saul and they and all the men of Israel were in the Valley of
        Elah, fighting with the Philistines.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So David rose early in the morning, left the sheep with a keeper,
        and took the  things and went as Jesse had commanded him. And he came to
        the camp as the army was going out to the fight and shouting for the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For Israel and the Philistines had drawn up in battle array, army
        against army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And David left his supplies in the hand of the supply keeper, ran
        to the army, and came and greeted his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then as he talked with them, there was the champion, the Philistine
        of Gath, Goliath by name, coming up from the armies of the Philistines; and
        he spoke according to the same words. So David heard them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And all the men of Israel, when they saw the man, fled from him and
        were dreadfully afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So the men of Israel said, \u201CHave you seen this man who has come
        up? Surely he has come up to defy Israel; and it shall be that the man who
        kills him the king will enrich with great riches, will give him his daughter,
        and give his father\u2019s house exemption from  taxes in Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then David spoke to the men who stood by him, saying, \u201CWhat
        shall be done for the man who kills this Philistine and takes away the reproach
        from Israel? For who is this uncircumcised Philistine, that he should defy
        the armies of the living God?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And the people answered him in this manner, saying, \u201CSo shall
        it be done for the man who kills him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now Eliab his oldest brother heard when he spoke to the men; and
        Eliab\u2019s anger was aroused against David, and he said, \u201CWhy did
        you come down here? And with whom have you left those few sheep in the wilderness?
        I know your pride and the insolence of your heart, for you have come down
        to see the battle.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And David said, \u201CWhat have I done now? Is there not a cause?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then he turned from him toward another and said the same thing; and
        these people answered him as the first ones did.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now when the words which David spoke were heard, they reported them
        to Saul; and he sent for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then David said to Saul, \u201CLet no man\u2019s heart fail because
        of him; your servant will go and fight with this Philistine.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And Saul said to David, \u201CYou are not able to go against this
        Philistine to fight with him; for you are a youth, and he a man of war from
        his youth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But David said to Saul, \u201CYour servant used to keep his father\u2019s
        sheep, and when a lion or a bear came and took a lamb out of the flock, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I went out after it and struck it, and delivered the  lamb from its
        mouth; and when it arose against me, I caught it by its beard, and struck
        and killed it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Your servant has killed both lion and bear; and this uncircumcised
        Philistine will be like one of them, seeing he has defied the armies of the
        living God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Moreover David said, \u201CThe Lord, who delivered me from the paw
        of the lion and from the paw of the bear, He will deliver me from the hand
        of this Philistine.\u201DAnd Saul said to David, \u201CGo, and the Lord be
        with you!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So Saul clothed David with his armor, and he put a bronze helmet
        on his head; he also clothed him with a coat of mail. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "David fastened his sword to his armor and tried to walk, for he had
        not tested them. And David said to Saul, \u201CI cannot walk with these,
        for I have not tested them.\u201D So David took them off."
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he took his staff in his hand; and he chose for himself five
        smooth stones from the brook, and put them in a shepherd\u2019s bag, in a
        pouch which he had, and his sling was in his hand. And he drew near to the
        Philistine. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'So the Philistine came, and began drawing near to David, and the
        man who bore the shield went before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And when the Philistine looked about and saw David, he disdained
        him; for he was only a youth, ruddy and good-looking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "So the Philistine said to David, \u201CAm I a dog, that you come
        to me with sticks?\u201D And the Philistine cursed David by his gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "And the Philistine said to David, \u201CCome to me, and I will give
        your flesh to the birds of the air and the beasts of the field!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Then David said to the Philistine, \u201CYou come to me with a sword,
        with a spear, and with a javelin. But I come to you in the name of the Lord
        of hosts, the God of the armies of Israel, whom you have defied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'This day the Lord will deliver you into my hand, and I will strike
        you and take your head from you. And this day I will give the carcasses of
        the camp of the Philistines to the birds of the air and the wild beasts of
        the earth, that all the earth may know that there is a God in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Then all this assembly shall know that the Lord  does not save with
        sword and spear; for the battle is the Lord\u2019s, and He will give you
        into our hands.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'So it was, when the Philistine arose and came and drew near to meet
        David, that David hurried and ran toward the army to meet the Philistine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Then David put his hand in his bag and took out a stone; and he slung
        it and struck the Philistine in his forehead, so that the stone sank into
        his forehead, and he fell on his face to the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'So David prevailed over the Philistine with a sling and a stone,
        and struck the Philistine and killed him. But there  was no sword in the
        hand of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Therefore David ran and stood over the Philistine, took his sword
        and drew it out of its sheath and killed him, and cut off his head with it.And
        when the Philistines saw that their champion was dead, they fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Now the men of Israel and Judah arose and shouted, and pursued the
        Philistines as far as the entrance of the valley and to the gates of Ekron.
        And the wounded of the Philistines fell along the road to Shaaraim, even
        as far as Gath and Ekron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Then the children of Israel returned from chasing the Philistines,
        and they plundered their tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: And David took the head of the Philistine and brought it to Jerusalem,
        but he put his armor in his tent.
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "When Saul saw David going out against the Philistine, he said to
        Abner, the commander of the army, \u201CAbner, whose son is this youth?\u201DAnd
        Abner said, \u201CAs your soul lives, O king, I do not know.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "So the king said, \u201CInquire whose son this young man is.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Then, as David returned from the slaughter of the Philistine, Abner
        took him and brought him before Saul with the head of the Philistine in his
        hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "And Saul said to him, \u201CWhose son are you, young man?\u201DSo
        David answered, \u201CI  am the son of your servant Jesse the Bethlehemite.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Resents David'
      title: Saul Resents David
      number: 1
      content: 'Now when he had finished speaking to Saul, the soul of Jonathan was
        knit to the soul of David, and Jonathan loved him as his own soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Saul took him that day, and would not let him go home to his father\u2019s
        house anymore. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jonathan and David made a covenant, because he loved him as
        his own soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And Jonathan took off the robe that was on him and gave it to David,
        with his armor, even to his sword and his bow and his belt.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David went out wherever Saul sent him, and behaved wisely. And
        Saul set him over the men of war, and he was accepted in the sight of all
        the people and also in the sight of Saul\u2019s servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now it had happened as they were coming home, when David was returning
        from the slaughter of the Philistine, that the women had come out of all
        the cities of Israel, singing and dancing, to meet King Saul, with tambourines,
        with joy, and with musical instruments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the women sang as they danced, and said:\u201CSaul has slain his
        thousands,And David his ten thousands.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Saul was very angry, and the saying displeased him; and he said,
        \u201CThey have ascribed to David ten thousands, and to me they have ascribed
        only thousands. Now what more can he have but the kingdom?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So Saul eyed David from that day forward.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And it happened on the next day that the distressing spirit from
        God came upon Saul, and he prophesied inside the house. So David played music
        with his hand, as at other times; but there  was a spear in Saul\u2019s hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Saul cast the spear, for he said, \u201CI will pin David to the
        wall!\u201D But David escaped his presence twice."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now Saul was afraid of David, because the Lord was with him, but
        had departed from Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore Saul removed him from his presence, and made him his captain
        over a thousand; and he went out and came in before the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And David behaved wisely in all his ways, and the Lord  was with
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore, when Saul saw that he behaved very wisely, he was afraid
        of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: David Marries Michal'
      title: David Marries Michal
      number: 16
      content: But all Israel and Judah loved David, because he went out and came
        in before them.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CHere is my older daughter Merab; I
        will give her to you as a wife. Only be valiant for me, and fight the Lord\u2019s
        battles.\u201D For Saul thought, \u201CLet my hand not be against him, but
        let the hand of the Philistines be against him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So David said to Saul, \u201CWho am I, and what is my life or my
        father\u2019s family in Israel, that I should be son-in-law to the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But it happened at the time when Merab, Saul\u2019s daughter, should
        have been given to David, that she was given to Adriel the Meholathite as
        a wife."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, loved David. And they told Saul,
        and the thing pleased him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So Saul said, \u201CI will give her to him, that she may be a snare
        to him, and that the hand of the Philistines may be against him.\u201D Therefore
        Saul said to David a second time, \u201CYou shall be my son-in-law today.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Saul commanded his servants, \u201CCommunicate with David secretly,
        and say, \u2018Look, the king has delight in you, and all his servants love
        you. Now therefore, become the king\u2019s son-in-law.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Saul\u2019s servants spoke those words in the hearing of David.
        And David said, \u201CDoes it seem to you a light thing to be a king\u2019s
        son-in-law, seeing I am a poor and lightly esteemed man?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the servants of Saul told him, saying, \u201CIn this manner David
        spoke.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CThus you shall say to David: \u2018The king
        does not desire any dowry but one hundred foreskins of the Philistines, to
        take vengeance on the king\u2019s enemies.\u2019 \u201D But Saul thought
        to make David fall by the hand of the Philistines. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So when his servants told David these words, it pleased David well
        to become the king\u2019s son-in-law. Now the days had not expired; "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "therefore David arose and went, he and his men, and killed two hundred
        men of the Philistines. And David brought their foreskins, and they gave
        them in full count to the king, that he might become the king\u2019s son-in-law.
        Then Saul gave him Michal his daughter as a wife."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Thus Saul saw and knew that the Lord  was with David, and that Michal,
        Saul\u2019s daughter, loved him; "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "and Saul was still more afraid of David. So Saul became David\u2019s
        enemy continually. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then the princes of the Philistines went out to  war. And so it was,
        whenever they went out, that David behaved more wisely than all the servants
        of Saul, so that his name became highly esteemed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Persecutes David'
      title: Saul Persecutes David
      number: 1
      content: "Now Saul spoke to Jonathan his son and to all his servants, that
        they should kill David; but Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, delighted greatly
        in David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Jonathan told David, saying, \u201CMy father Saul seeks to kill
        you. Therefore please be on your guard until morning, and stay in a secret
        place and hide. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I will go out and stand beside my father in the field where you
        are, and I will speak with my father about you. Then what I observe, I will
        tell you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus Jonathan spoke well of David to Saul his father, and said to
        him, \u201CLet not the king sin against his servant, against David, because
        he has not sinned against you, and because his works have  been very good
        toward you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For he took his life in his hands and killed the Philistine, and
        the Lord brought about a great deliverance for all Israel. You saw it and
        rejoiced. Why then will you sin against innocent blood, to kill David without
        a cause?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Saul heeded the voice of Jonathan, and Saul swore, \u201CAs the
        Lord lives, he shall not be killed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Then Jonathan called David, and Jonathan told him all these things.
        So Jonathan brought David to Saul, and he was in his presence as in times
        past.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And there was war again; and David went out and fought with the Philistines,
        and struck them with a mighty blow, and they fled from him.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now the distressing spirit from the Lord came upon Saul as he sat
        in his house with his spear in his hand. And David was playing music with
        his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Saul sought to pin David to the wall with the spear, but he
        slipped away from Saul\u2019s presence; and he drove the spear into the wall.
        So David fled and escaped that night."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Saul also sent messengers to David\u2019s house to watch him and
        to kill him in the morning. And Michal, David\u2019s wife, told him, saying,
        \u201CIf you do not save your life tonight, tomorrow you will be killed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Michal let David down through a window. And he went and fled and
        escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Michal took an image and laid it in the bed, put a cover of goats\u2019
        hair for his head, and covered it with clothes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So when Saul sent messengers to take David, she said, \u201CHe is
        sick.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Saul sent the messengers back to see David, saying, \u201CBring
        him up to me in the bed, that I may kill him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when the messengers had come in, there was the image in the bed,
        with a cover of goats\u2019 hair for his head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to Michal, \u201CWhy have you deceived me like this,
        and sent my enemy away, so that he has escaped?\u201DAnd Michal answered
        Saul, \u201CHe said to me, \u2018Let me go! Why should I kill you?\u2019
        \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So David fled and escaped, and went to Samuel at Ramah, and told
        him all that Saul had done to him. And he and Samuel went and stayed in Naioth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now it was told Saul, saying, \u201CTake note, David is at Naioth
        in Ramah!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Saul sent messengers to take David. And when they saw the group
        of prophets prophesying, and Samuel standing as leader over them, the Spirit
        of God came upon the messengers of Saul, and they also prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when Saul was told, he sent other messengers, and they prophesied
        likewise. Then Saul sent messengers again the third time, and they prophesied
        also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then he also went to Ramah, and came to the great well that is at
        Sechu. So he asked, and said, \u201CWhere are Samuel and David?\u201DAnd
        someone said, \u201CIndeed they  are at Naioth in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So he went there to Naioth in Ramah. Then the Spirit of God was upon
        him also, and he went on and prophesied until he came to Naioth in Ramah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And he also stripped off his clothes and prophesied before Samuel
        in like manner, and lay down naked all that day and all that night. Therefore
        they say, \u201CIs Saul also among the prophets?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jonathan\u2019s Loyalty to David"
      title: "Jonathan\u2019s Loyalty to David"
      number: 1
      content: "Then David fled from Naioth in Ramah, and went and said to Jonathan,
        \u201CWhat have I done? What is my iniquity, and what is my sin before your
        father, that he seeks my life?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Jonathan said to him, \u201CBy no means! You shall not die! Indeed,
        my father will do nothing either great or small without first telling me.
        And why should my father hide this thing from me? It is not so!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then David took an oath again, and said, \u201CYour father certainly
        knows that I have found favor in your eyes, and he has said, \u2018Do not
        let Jonathan know this, lest he be grieved.\u2019 But truly, as the Lord
        lives and as your soul lives, there  is but a step between me and death.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Jonathan said to David, \u201CWhatever you yourself desire, I
        will do it for you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And David said to Jonathan, \u201CIndeed tomorrow is the New Moon,
        and I should not fail to sit with the king to eat. But let me go, that I
        may hide in the field until the third day at evening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "If your father misses me at all, then say, \u2018David earnestly
        asked permission of me that he might run over to Bethlehem, his city, for
        there  is a yearly sacrifice there for all the family.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If he says thus: \u2018It  is well,\u2019 your servant will be safe.
        But if he is very angry, be sure that evil is determined by him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore you shall deal kindly with your servant, for you have brought
        your servant into a covenant of the Lord with you. Nevertheless, if there
        is iniquity in me, kill me yourself, for why should you bring me to your
        father?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But Jonathan said, \u201CFar be it from you! For if I knew certainly
        that evil was determined by my father to come upon you, then would I not
        tell you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David said to Jonathan, \u201CWho will tell me, or what if your
        father answers you roughly?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Jonathan said to David, \u201CCome, let us go out into the field.\u201D
        So both of them went out into the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David: \u201CThe Lord God of Israel is  witness!
        When I have sounded out my father sometime tomorrow, or the third day, and
        indeed there  is good toward David, and I do not send to you and tell you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'may the Lord do so and much more to Jonathan. But if it pleases my
        father to  do you evil, then I will report it to you and send you away, that
        you may go in safety. And the Lord be with you as He has been with my father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And you shall not only show me the kindness of the Lord while I still
        live, that I may not die; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but you shall not cut off your kindness from my house forever, no,
        not when the Lord has cut off every one of the enemies of David from the
        face of the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Jonathan made a  covenant with the house of David, saying,  \u201CLet
        the Lord require it at the hand of David\u2019s enemies.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now Jonathan again caused David to vow, because he loved him; for
        he loved him as he loved his own soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CTomorrow is the New Moon; and
        you will be missed, because your seat will be empty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And when you have stayed three days, go down quickly and come to
        the place where you hid on the day of the deed; and remain by the stone Ezel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then I will shoot three arrows to the side, as though I shot at a
        target; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "and there I will send a lad, saying, \u2018Go, find the arrows.\u2019
        If I expressly say to the lad, \u2018Look, the arrows are on this side of
        you; get them and come\u2019\u2014then, as the Lord lives, there  is safety
        for you and no harm. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But if I say thus to the young man, \u2018Look, the arrows are beyond
        you\u2019\u2014go your way, for the Lord has sent you away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And as for the matter which you and I have spoken of, indeed the
        Lord  be between you and me forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then David hid in the field. And when the New Moon had come, the
        king sat down to eat the feast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now the king sat on his seat, as at other times, on a seat by the
        wall. And Jonathan arose, and Abner sat by Saul\u2019s side, but David\u2019s
        place was empty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Nevertheless Saul did not say anything that day, for he thought,
        \u201CSomething has happened to him; he is unclean, surely he is  unclean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And it happened the next day, the second day of the month, that David\u2019s
        place was empty. And Saul said to Jonathan his son, \u201CWhy has the son
        of Jesse not come to eat, either yesterday or today?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Jonathan answered Saul, \u201CDavid earnestly asked permission
        of me to  go to Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And he said, \u2018Please let me go, for our family has a sacrifice
        in the city, and my brother has commanded me to  be  there. And now, if I
        have found favor in your eyes, please let me get away and see my brothers.\u2019
        Therefore he has not come to the king\u2019s table.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Saul\u2019s anger was aroused against Jonathan, and he said
        to him, \u201CYou son of a perverse, rebellious woman! Do I not know that
        you have chosen the son of Jesse to your own shame and to the shame of your
        mother\u2019s nakedness? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For as long as the son of Jesse lives on the earth, you shall not
        be established, nor your kingdom. Now therefore, send and bring him to me,
        for he shall surely die.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And Jonathan answered Saul his father, and said to him, \u201CWhy
        should he be killed? What has he done?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Then Saul cast a spear at him to kill him, by which Jonathan knew
        that it was determined by his father to kill David.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: So Jonathan arose from the table in fierce anger, and ate no food
        the second day of the month, for he was grieved for David, because his father
        had treated him shamefully.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And so it was, in the morning, that Jonathan went out into the field
        at the time appointed with David, and a little lad was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then he said to his lad, \u201CNow run, find the arrows which I shoot.\u201D
        As the lad ran, he shot an arrow beyond him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "When the lad had come to the place where the arrow was which Jonathan
        had shot, Jonathan cried out after the lad and said, \u201CIs not the arrow
        beyond you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Jonathan cried out after the lad, \u201CMake haste, hurry, do
        not delay!\u201D So Jonathan\u2019s lad gathered up the arrows and came back
        to his master. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But the lad did not know anything. Only Jonathan and David knew of
        the matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then Jonathan gave his weapons to his lad, and said to him, \u201CGo,
        carry them to the city.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'As soon as the lad had gone, David arose from a  place toward the
        south, fell on his face to the ground, and bowed down three times. And they
        kissed one another; and they wept together, but David more so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CGo in peace, since we have both
        sworn in the name of the Lord, saying, \u2018May the Lord be between you
        and me, and between your descendants and my descendants, forever.\u2019 \u201D
        So he arose and departed, and Jonathan went into the city."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David and the Holy Bread'
      title: David and the Holy Bread
      number: 1
      content: "Now David came to Nob, to Ahimelech the priest. And Ahimelech was
        afraid when he met David, and said to him, \u201CWhy are you alone, and no
        one is with you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So David said to Ahimelech the priest, \u201CThe king has ordered
        me on some business, and said to me, \u2018Do not let anyone know anything
        about the business on which I send you, or what I have commanded you.\u2019
        And I have directed my young men to such and such a place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now therefore, what have you on hand? Give me five loaves  of bread
        in my hand, or whatever can be found.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the priest answered David and said, \u201CThere  is no common
        bread on hand; but there is holy bread, if the young men have at least kept
        themselves from women.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David answered the priest, and said to him, \u201CTruly, women
        have  been kept from us about three days since I came out. And the vessels
        of the young men are holy, and the  bread  is in effect common, even though
        it was consecrated in the vessel this day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So the priest gave him holy bread; for there was no bread there but
        the showbread which had been taken from before the Lord, in order to put
        hot bread in  its  place on the day when it was taken away.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Now a certain man of the servants of Saul was there that day, detained
        before the Lord. And his name was  Doeg, an Edomite, the chief of the herdsmen
        who belonged to Saul.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And David said to Ahimelech, \u201CIs there not here on hand a spear
        or a sword? For I have brought neither my sword nor my weapons with me, because
        the king\u2019s business required haste.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: David Flees to Gath'
      title: David Flees to Gath
      number: 9
      content: "So the priest said, \u201CThe sword of Goliath the Philistine, whom
        you killed in the Valley of Elah, there it is, wrapped in a cloth behind
        the ephod. If you will take that, take it. For there  is no other except
        that one here.\u201DAnd David said, \u201CThere  is none like it; give it
        to me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then David arose and fled that day from before Saul, and went to
        Achish the king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the servants of Achish said to him, \u201CIs this not David the
        king of the land? Did they not sing of him to one another in dances, saying:\u2018Saul
        has slain his thousands,And David his ten thousands\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now David took these words to heart, and was very much afraid of
        Achish the king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So he changed his behavior before them, pretended madness in their
        hands, scratched on the doors of the gate, and let his saliva fall down on
        his beard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Achish said to his servants, \u201CLook, you see the man is
        insane. Why have you brought him to me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Have I need of madmen, that you have brought this fellow to play
        the madman in my presence? Shall this fellow come into my house?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Four Hundred Men"
      title: "David\u2019s Four Hundred Men"
      number: 1
      content: "David therefore departed from there and escaped to the cave of Adullam.
        So when his brothers and all his father\u2019s house heard it, they went
        down there to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And everyone who  was in distress, everyone who was in debt, and everyone
        who  was discontented gathered to him. So he became captain over them. And
        there were about four hundred men with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then David went from there to Mizpah of Moab; and he said to the
        king of Moab, \u201CPlease let my father and mother come here with you, till
        I know what God will do for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So he brought them before the king of Moab, and they dwelt with him
        all the time that David was in the stronghold.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Saul Murders the Priests'
      title: Saul Murders the Priests
      number: 5
      content: "Now the prophet Gad said to David, \u201CDo not stay in the stronghold;
        depart, and go to the land of Judah.\u201D So David departed and went into
        the forest of Hereth."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When Saul heard that David and the men who were with him had been
        discovered\u2014now Saul was staying in Gibeah under a tamarisk tree in Ramah,
        with his spear in his hand, and all his servants standing about him\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "then Saul said to his servants who stood about him, \u201CHear now,
        you Benjamites! Will the son of Jesse give every one of you fields and vineyards,
        and make you all captains of thousands and captains of hundreds? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All of you have conspired against me, and there  is no one who reveals
        to me that my son has made a covenant with the son of Jesse; and there  is
        not one of you who is sorry for me or reveals to me that my son has stirred
        up my servant against me, to lie in wait, as it  is this day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then answered Doeg the Edomite, who was set over the servants of
        Saul, and said, \u201CI saw the son of Jesse going to Nob, to Ahimelech the
        son of Ahitub. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he inquired of the Lord for him, gave him provisions, and gave
        him the sword of Goliath the Philistine.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the king sent to call Ahimelech the priest, the son of Ahitub,
        and all his father\u2019s house, the priests who were in Nob. And they all
        came to the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CHear now, son of Ahitub!\u201DHe answered, \u201CHere
        I am, my lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Saul said to him, \u201CWhy have you conspired against me, you
        and the son of Jesse, in that you have given him bread and a sword, and have
        inquired of God for him, that he should rise against me, to lie in wait,
        as it is this day?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Ahimelech answered the king and said, \u201CAnd who among all
        your servants is  as  faithful as David, who is the king\u2019s son-in-law,
        who goes at your bidding, and is honorable in your house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Did I then begin to inquire of God for him? Far be it from me! Let
        not the king impute anything to his servant, or to any in the house of my
        father. For your servant knew nothing of all this, little or much.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the king said, \u201CYou shall surely die, Ahimelech, you and
        all your father\u2019s house!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the king said to the guards who stood about him, \u201CTurn
        and kill the priests of the Lord, because their hand also is with David,
        and because they knew when he fled and did not tell it to me.\u201D But the
        servants of the king would not lift their hands to strike the priests of
        the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the king said to Doeg, \u201CYou turn and kill the priests!\u201D
        So Doeg the Edomite turned and struck the priests, and killed on that day
        eighty-five men who wore a linen ephod. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Also Nob, the city of the priests, he struck with the edge of the
        sword, both men and women, children and nursing infants, oxen and donkeys
        and sheep\u2014with the edge of the sword."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now one of the sons of Ahimelech the son of Ahitub, named Abiathar,
        escaped and fled after David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Abiathar told David that Saul had killed the Lord\u2019s priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So David said to Abiathar, \u201CI knew that day, when Doeg the Edomite
        was there, that he would surely tell Saul. I have caused the  death of all
        the persons of your father\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Stay with me; do not fear. For he who seeks my life seeks your life,
        but with me you shall  be safe.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Saves the City of Keilah'
      title: David Saves the City of Keilah
      number: 1
      content: "Then they told David, saying, \u201CLook, the Philistines are fighting
        against Keilah, and they are robbing the threshing floors.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore David inquired of the Lord, saying, \u201CShall I go and
        attack these Philistines?\u201DAnd the Lord said to David, \u201CGo and attack
        the Philistines, and save Keilah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But David\u2019s men said to him, \u201CLook, we are afraid here
        in Judah. How much more then if we go to Keilah against the armies of the
        Philistines?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then David inquired of the Lord once again.And the Lord answered
        him and said, \u201CArise, go down to Keilah. For I will deliver the Philistines
        into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: And David and his men went to Keilah and fought with the Philistines,
        struck them with a mighty blow, and took away their livestock. So David saved
        the inhabitants of Keilah.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Now it happened, when Abiathar the son of Ahimelech fled to David
        at Keilah, that he went down with an ephod in his hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Saul was told that David had gone to Keilah. So Saul said, \u201CGod
        has delivered him into my hand, for he has shut himself in by entering a
        town that has gates and bars.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Then Saul called all the people together for war, to go down to Keilah
        to besiege David and his men.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When David knew that Saul plotted evil against him, he said to Abiathar
        the priest, \u201CBring the ephod here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David said, \u201CO Lord God of Israel, Your servant has certainly
        heard that Saul seeks to come to Keilah to destroy the city for my sake. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Will the men of Keilah deliver me into his hand? Will Saul come down,
        as Your servant has heard? O Lord God of Israel, I pray, tell Your servant.\u201DAnd
        the Lord said, \u201CHe will come down.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then David said, \u201CWill the men of Keilah deliver me and my men
        into the hand of Saul?\u201DAnd the Lord said, \u201CThey will deliver you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: David in Wilderness Strongholds'
      title: David in Wilderness Strongholds
      number: 13
      content: So David and his men, about six hundred, arose and departed from Keilah
        and went wherever they could go. Then it was told Saul that David had escaped
        from Keilah; so he halted the expedition.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And David stayed in strongholds in the wilderness, and remained in
        the mountains in the Wilderness of Ziph. Saul sought him every day, but God
        did not deliver him into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So David saw that Saul had come out to seek his life. And David was
        in the Wilderness of Ziph in a forest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, arose and went to David in the woods
        and strengthened his hand in God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CDo not fear, for the hand of Saul my father
        shall not find you. You shall be king over Israel, and I shall be next to
        you. Even my father Saul knows that.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: So the two of them made a covenant before the Lord. And David stayed
        in the woods, and Jonathan went to his own house.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Ziphites came up to Saul at Gibeah, saying, \u201CIs David
        not hiding with us in strongholds in the woods, in the hill of Hachilah,
        which is on the south of Jeshimon? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now therefore, O king, come down according to all the desire of your
        soul to come down; and our part shall  be to deliver him into the king\u2019s
        hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Saul said, \u201CBlessed are you of the Lord, for you have compassion
        on me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Please go and find out for sure, and see the place where his hideout
        is, and who has seen him there. For I am told he is very crafty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "See therefore, and take knowledge of all the lurking places where
        he hides; and come back to me with certainty, and I will go with you. And
        it shall be, if he is in the land, that I will search for him throughout
        all the clans of Judah.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So they arose and went to Ziph before Saul. But David and his men
        were in the Wilderness of Maon, in the plain on the south of Jeshimon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When Saul and his men went to seek him, they told David. Therefore
        he went down to the rock, and stayed in the Wilderness of Maon. And when
        Saul heard that, he pursued David in the Wilderness of Maon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Then Saul went on one side of the mountain, and David and his men
        on the other side of the mountain. So David made haste to get away from Saul,
        for Saul and his men were encircling David and his men to take them.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But a messenger came to Saul, saying, \u201CHurry and come, for the
        Philistines have invaded the land!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Therefore Saul returned from pursuing David, and went against the
        Philistines; so they called that place the Rock of Escape. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Then David went up from there and dwelt in strongholds at En Gedi.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Spares Saul'
      title: David Spares Saul
      number: 1
      content: "Now it happened, when Saul had returned from following the Philistines,
        that it was told him, saying, \u201CTake note! David is in the Wilderness
        of En Gedi.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Saul took three thousand chosen men from all Israel, and went
        to seek David and his men on the Rocks of the Wild Goats. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So he came to the sheepfolds by the road, where there was a cave;
        and Saul went in to attend to his needs. (David and his men were staying
        in the recesses of the cave.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the men of David said to him, \u201CThis is the day of which
        the Lord said to you, \u2018Behold, I will deliver your enemy into your hand,
        that you may do to him as it seems good to you.\u2019 \u201D And David arose
        and secretly cut off a corner of Saul\u2019s robe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now it happened afterward that David\u2019s heart troubled him because
        he had cut Saul\u2019s robe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to his men, \u201CThe Lord forbid that I should do this
        thing to my master, the Lord\u2019s anointed, to stretch out my hand against
        him, seeing he is the anointed of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: So David restrained his servants with these words, and did not allow
        them to rise against Saul. And Saul got up from the cave and went on his
        way.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David also arose afterward, went out of the cave, and called out
        to Saul, saying, \u201CMy lord the king!\u201D And when Saul looked behind
        him, David stooped with his face to the earth, and bowed down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And David said to Saul: \u201CWhy do you listen to the words of men
        who say, \u2018Indeed David seeks your harm\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Look, this day your eyes have seen that the Lord delivered you today
        into my hand in the cave, and someone urged me to kill you. But my  eye spared
        you, and I said, \u2018I will not stretch out my hand against my lord, for
        he is the Lord\u2019s anointed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moreover, my father, see! Yes, see the corner of your robe in my
        hand! For in that I cut off the corner of your robe, and did not kill you,
        know and see that there  is  neither evil nor rebellion in my hand, and I
        have not sinned against you. Yet you hunt my life to take it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let the Lord judge between you and me, and let the Lord avenge me
        on you. But my hand shall not be against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As the proverb of the ancients says, \u2018Wickedness proceeds from
        the wicked.\u2019 But my hand shall not be against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After whom has the king of Israel come out? Whom do you pursue? A
        dead dog? A flea? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore let the Lord be judge, and judge between you and me, and
        see and plead my case, and deliver me out of your hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So it was, when David had finished speaking these words to Saul,
        that Saul said, \u201CIs this your voice, my son David?\u201D And Saul lifted
        up his voice and wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then he said to David: \u201CYou are  more righteous than I; for
        you have rewarded me with good, whereas I have rewarded you with evil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And you have shown this day how you have dealt well with me; for
        when the Lord delivered me into your hand, you did not kill me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For if a man finds his enemy, will he let him get away safely? Therefore
        may the Lord reward you with good for what you have done to me this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And now I know indeed that you shall surely be king, and that the
        kingdom of Israel shall be established in your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore swear now to me by the Lord  that you will not cut off
        my descendants after me, and that you will not destroy my name from my father\u2019s
        house.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So David swore to Saul. And Saul went home, but David and his men
        went up to the stronghold.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Death of SamuelDavid and the Wife of Nabal'
      title: Death of SamuelDavid and the Wife of Nabal
      number: 1
      content: Then Samuel died; and the Israelites gathered together and lamented
        for him, and buried him at his home in Ramah. And David arose and went down
        to the Wilderness of Paran.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now there  was a man in Maon whose business was in Carmel, and the
        man was very rich. He had three thousand sheep and a thousand goats. And
        he was shearing his sheep in Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The name of the man was Nabal, and the name of his wife Abigail. And
        she  was a woman of good understanding and beautiful appearance; but the
        man was harsh and evil in his doings. He was  of  the  house  of  Caleb.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When David heard in the wilderness that Nabal was shearing his sheep, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David sent ten young men; and David said to the young men, \u201CGo
        up to Carmel, go to Nabal, and greet him in my name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And thus you shall say to him who lives in  prosperity:  \u2018Peace
        be to you, peace to your house, and peace to all that you have! "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now I have heard that you have shearers. Your shepherds were with
        us, and we did not hurt them, nor was there anything missing from them all
        the while they were in Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ask your young men, and they will tell you. Therefore let my young
        men find favor in your eyes, for we come on a feast day. Please give whatever
        comes to your hand to your servants and to your son David.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So when David\u2019s young men came, they spoke to Nabal according
        to all these words in the name of David, and waited."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Nabal answered David\u2019s servants, and said, \u201CWho is
        David, and who is the son of Jesse? There are many servants nowadays who
        break away each one from his master. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Shall I then take my bread and my water and my meat that I have killed
        for my shearers, and give it to men when I do not know where they are from?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David\u2019s young men turned on their heels and went back; and
        they came and told him all these words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to his men, \u201CEvery man gird on his sword.\u201D
        So every man girded on his sword, and David also girded on his sword. And
        about four hundred men went with David, and two hundred stayed with the supplies."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now one of the young men told Abigail, Nabal\u2019s wife, saying,
        \u201CLook, David sent messengers from the wilderness to greet our master;
        and he reviled them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But the men were very good to us, and we were not hurt, nor did we
        miss anything as long as we accompanied them, when we were in the fields. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They were a wall to us both by night and day, all the time we were
        with them keeping the sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now therefore, know and consider what you will do, for harm is determined
        against our master and against all his household. For he is  such a scoundrel
        that one cannot speak to him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Abigail made haste and took two hundred loaves of bread, two
        skins of wine, five sheep already dressed, five seahs of roasted grain, one
        hundred clusters of raisins, and two hundred cakes of figs, and loaded them
        on donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And she said to her servants, \u201CGo on before me; see, I am coming
        after you.\u201D But she did not tell her husband Nabal."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So it was, as she rode on the donkey, that she went down under cover
        of the hill; and there were David and his men, coming down toward her, and
        she met them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now David had said, \u201CSurely in vain I have protected all that
        this fellow has in the wilderness, so that nothing was missed of all that
        belongs to him. And he has repaid me evil for good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "May God do so, and more also, to the enemies of David, if I leave
        one male of all who belong to him by morning light.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now when Abigail saw David, she dismounted quickly from the donkey,
        fell on her face before David, and bowed down to the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So she fell at his feet and said: \u201COn me, my lord, on me let
        this iniquity be! And please let your maidservant speak in your ears, and
        hear the words of your maidservant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Please, let not my lord regard this scoundrel Nabal. For as his name
        is, so is he: Nabal is his name, and folly is with him! But I, your maidservant,
        did not see the young men of my lord whom you sent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now therefore, my lord, as the Lord lives and as your soul lives,
        since the Lord has held you back from coming to bloodshed and from avenging
        yourself with your own hand, now then, let your enemies and those who seek
        harm for my lord be as Nabal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And now this present which your maidservant has brought to my lord,
        let it be given to the young men who follow my lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Please forgive the trespass of your maidservant. For the Lord will
        certainly make for my lord an enduring house, because my lord fights the
        battles of the Lord, and evil is not found in you throughout your days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Yet a man has risen to pursue you and seek your life, but the life
        of my lord shall be bound in the bundle of the living with the Lord your
        God; and the lives of your enemies He shall sling out, as  from the pocket
        of a sling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And it shall come to pass, when the Lord has done for my lord according
        to all the good that He has spoken concerning you, and has appointed you
        ruler over Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "that this will be no grief to you, nor offense of heart to my lord,
        either that you have shed blood without cause, or that my lord has avenged
        himself. But when the Lord has dealt well with my lord, then remember your
        maidservant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then David said to Abigail: \u201CBlessed is the Lord God of Israel,
        who sent you this day to meet me! "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And blessed is your advice and blessed are you, because you have
        kept me this day from coming to bloodshed and from avenging myself with my
        own hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For indeed, as the Lord God of Israel lives, who has kept me back
        from hurting you, unless you had hurried and come to meet me, surely by morning
        light no males would have been left to Nabal!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "So David received from her hand what she had brought him, and said
        to her, \u201CGo up in peace to your house. See, I have heeded your voice
        and respected your person.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Now Abigail went to Nabal, and there he was, holding a feast in his
        house, like the feast of a king. And Nabal\u2019s heart was merry within
        him, for he was very drunk; therefore she told him nothing, little or much,
        until morning light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So it was, in the morning, when the wine had gone from Nabal, and
        his wife had told him these things, that his heart died within him, and he
        became like a stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: Then it happened, after about ten days, that the Lord  struck Nabal,
        and he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "So when David heard that Nabal was dead, he said, \u201CBlessed be
        the Lord, who has pleaded the cause of my reproach from the hand of Nabal,
        and has kept His servant from evil! For the Lord has returned the wickedness
        of Nabal on his own head.\u201DAnd David sent and proposed to Abigail, to
        take her as his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "When the servants of David had come to Abigail at Carmel, they spoke
        to her saying, \u201CDavid sent us to you, to ask you to become his wife.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Then she arose, bowed her face to the earth, and said, \u201CHere
        is your maidservant, a servant to wash the feet of the servants of my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So Abigail rose in haste and rode on a donkey, attended by five of
        her maidens; and she followed the messengers of David, and became his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: David also took Ahinoam of Jezreel, and so both of them were his wives.
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "But Saul had given Michal his daughter, David\u2019s wife, to Palti
        the son of Laish, who was from Gallim."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Spares Saul a Second Time'
      title: David Spares Saul a Second Time
      number: 1
      content: "Now the Ziphites came to Saul at Gibeah, saying, \u201CIs David not
        hiding in the hill of Hachilah, opposite Jeshimon?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Saul arose and went down to the Wilderness of Ziph, having three
        thousand chosen men of Israel with him, to seek David in the Wilderness of
        Ziph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Saul encamped in the hill of Hachilah, which is opposite Jeshimon,
        by the road. But David stayed in the wilderness, and he saw that Saul came
        after him into the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: David therefore sent out spies, and understood that Saul had indeed
        come.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So David arose and came to the place where Saul had encamped. And
        David saw the place where Saul lay, and Abner the son of Ner, the commander
        of his army. Now Saul lay within the camp, with the people encamped all around
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David answered, and said to Ahimelech the Hittite and to Abishai
        the son of Zeruiah, brother of Joab, saying, \u201CWho will go down with
        me to Saul in the camp?\u201DAnd Abishai said, \u201CI will go down with
        you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So David and Abishai came to the people by night; and there Saul
        lay sleeping within the camp, with his spear stuck in the ground by his head.
        And Abner and the people lay all around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abishai said to David, \u201CGod has delivered your enemy into
        your hand this day. Now therefore, please, let me strike him at once with
        the spear, right to the earth; and I will not have  to  strike him a second
        time!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But David said to Abishai, \u201CDo not destroy him; for who can
        stretch out his hand against the Lord\u2019s anointed, and be guiltless?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "David said furthermore, \u201CAs the Lord lives, the Lord shall strike
        him, or his day shall come to die, or he shall go out to battle and perish. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Lord forbid that I should stretch out my hand against the Lord\u2019s
        anointed. But please, take now the spear and the jug of water that are by
        his head, and let us go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David took the spear and the jug of water by Saul\u2019s head,
        and they got away; and no man saw or knew it or awoke. For they were all
        asleep, because a deep sleep from the Lord had fallen on them."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now David went over to the other side, and stood on the top of a
        hill afar off, a great distance being between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And David called out to the people and to Abner the son of Ner, saying,
        \u201CDo you not answer, Abner?\u201DThen Abner answered and said, \u201CWho
        are you, calling out to the king?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So David said to Abner, \u201CAre you not a man? And who is like
        you in Israel? Why then have you not guarded your lord the king? For one
        of the people came in to destroy your lord the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This thing that you have done is not good. As the Lord lives, you
        deserve to die, because you have not guarded your master, the Lord\u2019s
        anointed. And now see where the king\u2019s spear is, and the jug of water
        that was by his head.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul knew David\u2019s voice, and said, \u201CIs that your voice,
        my son David?\u201DDavid said, \u201CIt  is my voice, my lord, O king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhy does my lord thus pursue his servant? For
        what have I done, or what evil is in my hand? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now therefore, please, let my lord the king hear the words of his
        servant: If the Lord has stirred you up against me, let Him accept an offering.
        But if it  is the children of men, may they be cursed before the Lord, for
        they have driven me out this day from sharing in the inheritance of the Lord,
        saying, \u2018Go, serve other gods.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So now, do not let my blood fall to the earth before the face of
        the Lord. For the king of Israel has come out to seek a flea, as when one
        hunts a partridge in the mountains.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CI have sinned. Return, my son David. For I
        will harm you no more, because my life was precious in your eyes this day.
        Indeed I have played the fool and erred exceedingly.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And David answered and said, \u201CHere is the king\u2019s spear.
        Let one of the young men come over and get it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "May the Lord  repay every man for his righteousness and his faithfulness;
        for the Lord delivered you into my hand today, but I would not stretch out
        my hand against the Lord\u2019s anointed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And indeed, as your life was valued much this day in my eyes, so
        let my life be valued much in the eyes of the Lord, and let Him deliver me
        out of all tribulation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CMay you be blessed, my son David!
        You shall both do great things and also still prevail.\u201DSo David went
        on his way, and Saul returned to his place."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Allied with the Philistines'
      title: David Allied with the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: "And David said in his heart, \u201CNow I shall perish someday by
        the hand of Saul. There  is nothing better for me than that I should speedily
        escape to the land of the Philistines; and Saul will despair of me, to seek
        me anymore in any part of Israel. So I shall escape out of his hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then David arose and went over with the six hundred men who were
        with him to Achish the son of Maoch, king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So David dwelt with Achish at Gath, he and his men, each man with
        his household, and David with his two wives, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and
        Abigail the Carmelitess, Nabal\u2019s widow. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And it was told Saul that David had fled to Gath; so he sought him
        no more.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David said to Achish, \u201CIf I have now found favor in your
        eyes, let them give me a place in some town in the country, that I may dwell
        there. For why should your servant dwell in the royal city with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Achish gave him Ziklag that day. Therefore Ziklag has belonged
        to the kings of Judah to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Now the time that David dwelt in the country of the Philistines was
        one full year and four months.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And David and his men went up and raided the Geshurites, the Girzites,
        and the Amalekites. For those nations were the inhabitants of the land from
        of old, as you go to Shur, even as far as the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Whenever David attacked the land, he left neither man nor woman alive,
        but took away the sheep, the oxen, the donkeys, the camels, and the apparel,
        and returned and came to Achish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Achish would say, \u201CWhere have you made a raid today?\u201D
        And David would say, \u201CAgainst the southern area of Judah, or against
        the southern area of the Jerahmeelites, or against the southern area of the
        Kenites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "David would save neither man nor woman alive, to bring news to Gath,
        saying, \u201CLest they should inform on us, saying, \u2018Thus David did.\u2019
        \u201D And thus was his behavior all the time he dwelt in the country of
        the Philistines. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Achish believed David, saying, \u201CHe has made his people Israel
        utterly abhor him; therefore he will be my servant forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Now it happened in those days that the Philistines gathered their
        armies together for war, to fight with Israel. And Achish said to David,
        \u201CYou assuredly know that you will go out with me to battle, you and
        your men.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Saul Consults a Medium'
      title: Saul Consults a Medium
      number: 2
      content: "So David said to Achish, \u201CSurely you know what your servant
        can do.\u201DAnd Achish said to David, \u201CTherefore I will make you one
        of my chief guardians forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Now Samuel had died, and all Israel had lamented for him and buried
        him in Ramah, in his own city. And Saul had put the mediums and the spiritists
        out of the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the Philistines gathered together, and came and encamped at
        Shunem. So Saul gathered all Israel together, and they encamped at Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Saul saw the army of the Philistines, he was afraid, and his
        heart trembled greatly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And when Saul inquired of the Lord, the Lord did not answer him, either
        by dreams or by Urim or by the prophets.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Saul said to his servants, \u201CFind me a woman who is a medium,
        that I may go to her and inquire of her.\u201DAnd his servants said to him,
        \u201CIn fact, there  is a woman who is a medium at En Dor.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Saul disguised himself and put on other clothes, and he went,
        and two men with him; and they came to the woman by night. And he said, \u201CPlease
        conduct a s\xE9ance for me, and bring up for me the one I shall name to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the woman said to him, \u201CLook, you know what Saul has done,
        how he has cut off the mediums and the spiritists from the land. Why then
        do you lay a snare for my life, to cause me to die?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Saul swore to her by the Lord, saying, \u201CAs the Lord lives,
        no punishment shall come upon you for this thing.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the woman said, \u201CWhom shall I bring up for you?\u201DAnd
        he said, \u201CBring up Samuel for me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When the woman saw Samuel, she cried out with a loud voice. And the
        woman spoke to Saul, saying, \u201CWhy have you deceived me? For you are
        Saul!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the king said to her, \u201CDo not be afraid. What did you see?\u201DAnd
        the woman said to Saul, \u201CI saw a spirit ascending out of the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So he said to her, \u201CWhat is his form?\u201DAnd she said, \u201CAn
        old man is coming up, and he is covered with a mantle.\u201D And Saul perceived
        that it was Samuel, and he stooped with his face to the ground and bowed
        down."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now Samuel said to Saul, \u201CWhy have you disturbed me by bringing
        me up?\u201DAnd Saul answered, \u201CI am deeply distressed; for the Philistines
        make war against me, and God has departed from me and does not answer me
        anymore, neither by prophets nor by dreams. Therefore I have called you,
        that you may reveal to me what I should do.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samuel said: \u201CSo why do you ask me, seeing the Lord has
        departed from you and has become your enemy? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the Lord has done for Himself as He spoke by me. For the Lord
        has torn the kingdom out of your hand and given it to your neighbor, David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Because you did not obey the voice of the Lord nor execute His fierce
        wrath upon Amalek, therefore the Lord has done this thing to you this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Moreover the Lord will also deliver Israel with you into the hand
        of the Philistines. And tomorrow you and your sons will  be with me. The
        Lord will also deliver the army of Israel into the hand of the Philistines.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Immediately Saul fell full length on the ground, and was dreadfully
        afraid because of the words of Samuel. And there was no strength in him,
        for he had eaten no food all day or all night.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the woman came to Saul and saw that he was severely troubled,
        and said to him, \u201CLook, your maidservant has obeyed your voice, and
        I have put my life in my hands and heeded the words which you spoke to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now therefore, please, heed also the voice of your maidservant, and
        let me set a piece of bread before you; and eat, that you may have strength
        when you go on your way.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But he refused and said, \u201CI will not eat.\u201DSo his servants,
        together with the woman, urged him; and he heeded their voice. Then he arose
        from the ground and sat on the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now the woman had a fatted calf in the house, and she hastened to
        kill it. And she took flour and kneaded it, and baked unleavened bread from
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So she brought it before Saul and his servants, and they ate. Then
        they rose and went away that night.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Philistines Reject David'
      title: The Philistines Reject David
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the Philistines gathered together all their armies at Aphek,
        and the Israelites encamped by a fountain which is in Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the lords of the Philistines passed in review by hundreds and
        by thousands, but David and his men passed in review at the rear with Achish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the princes of the Philistines said, \u201CWhat are these Hebrews
        doing  here?\u201DAnd Achish said to the princes of the Philistines, \u201CIs
        this not David, the servant of Saul king of Israel, who has been with me
        these days, or these years? And to this day I have found no fault in him
        since he defected to  me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the princes of the Philistines were angry with him; so the princes
        of the Philistines said to him, \u201CMake this fellow return, that he may
        go back to the place which you have appointed for him, and do not let him
        go down with us to battle, lest in the battle he become our adversary. For
        with what could he reconcile himself to his master, if not with the heads
        of these men? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Is this not David, of whom they sang to one another in dances, saying:\u2018Saul
        has slain his thousands,And David his ten thousands\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Achish called David and said to him, \u201CSurely, as the Lord
        lives, you have been upright, and your going out and your coming in with
        me in the army is good in my sight. For to this day I have not found evil
        in you since the day of your coming to me. Nevertheless the lords do not
        favor you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore return now, and go in peace, that you may not displease
        the lords of the Philistines.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So David said to Achish, \u201CBut what have I done? And to this
        day what have you found in your servant as long as I have been with you,
        that I may not go and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Achish answered and said to David, \u201CI know that you are
        as good in my sight as an angel of God; nevertheless the princes of the Philistines
        have said, \u2018He shall not go up with us to the battle.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now therefore, rise early in the morning with your master\u2019s
        servants who have come with you. And as soon as you are up early in the morning
        and have light, depart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So David and his men rose early to depart in the morning, to return
        to the land of the Philistines. And the Philistines went up to Jezreel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Conflict with the Amalekites"
      title: "David\u2019s Conflict with the Amalekites"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it happened, when David and his men came to Ziklag, on the third
        day, that the Amalekites had invaded the South and Ziklag, attacked Ziklag
        and burned it with fire, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and had taken captive the women and those who were there, from small
        to great; they did not kill anyone, but carried them away and went their
        way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So David and his men came to the city, and there it was, burned with
        fire; and their wives, their sons, and their daughters had been taken captive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then David and the people who were with him lifted up their voices
        and wept, until they had no more power to weep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And David\u2019s two wives, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail
        the widow of Nabal the Carmelite, had been taken captive. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Now David was greatly distressed, for the people spoke of stoning
        him, because the soul of all the people was grieved, every man for his sons
        and his daughters. But David strengthened himself in the Lord his God.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then David said to Abiathar the priest, Ahimelech\u2019s son, \u201CPlease
        bring the ephod here to me.\u201D And Abiathar brought the ephod to David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So David inquired of the Lord, saying, \u201CShall I pursue this
        troop? Shall I overtake them?\u201DAnd He answered him, \u201CPursue, for
        you shall surely overtake them and without fail recover all.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So David went, he and the six hundred men who were with him, and
        came to the Brook Besor, where those stayed who were left behind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: But David pursued, he and four hundred men; for two hundred stayed
        behind, who were so weary that they could not cross the Brook Besor.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they found an Egyptian in the field, and brought him to David;
        and they gave him bread and he ate, and they let him drink water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And they gave him a piece of a cake of figs and two clusters of raisins.
        So when he had eaten, his strength came back to him; for he had eaten no
        bread nor drunk water for three days and three nights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then David said to him, \u201CTo whom do you belong, and where are
        you from?\u201DAnd he said, \u201CI am a young man from Egypt, servant of
        an Amalekite; and my master left me behind, because three days ago I fell
        sick. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "We made an invasion of the southern area of the Cherethites, in the
        territory which belongs to Judah, and of the southern area  of Caleb; and
        we burned Ziklag with fire.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And David said to him, \u201CCan you take me down to this troop?\u201DSo
        he said, \u201CSwear to me by God that you will neither kill me nor deliver
        me into the hands of my master, and I will take you down to this troop.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when he had brought him down, there they were, spread out over
        all the land, eating and drinking and dancing, because of all the great spoil
        which they had taken from the land of the Philistines and from the land of
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then David attacked them from twilight until the evening of the next
        day. Not a man of them escaped, except four hundred young men who rode on
        camels and fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So David recovered all that the Amalekites had carried away, and
        David rescued his two wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And nothing of theirs was lacking, either small or great, sons or
        daughters, spoil or anything which they had taken from them; David recovered
        all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then David took all the flocks and herds they had driven before those
        other livestock, and said, \u201CThis is David\u2019s spoil.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now David came to the two hundred men who had been so weary that
        they could not follow David, whom they also had made to stay at the Brook
        Besor. So they went out to meet David and to meet the people who were with
        him. And when David came near the people, he greeted them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then all the wicked and worthless men of those who went with David
        answered and said, \u201CBecause they did not go with us, we will not give
        them any of the spoil that we have recovered, except for every man\u2019s
        wife and children, that they may lead them away and depart.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But David said, \u201CMy brethren, you shall not do so with what
        the Lord has given us, who has preserved us and delivered into our hand the
        troop that came against us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "For who will heed you in this matter? But as his part is who goes
        down to the battle, so shall his part be who stays by the supplies; they
        shall share alike.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: So it was, from that day forward; he made it a statute and an ordinance
        for Israel to this day.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Now when David came to Ziklag, he sent some of the spoil to the elders
        of Judah, to his friends, saying, \u201CHere is a present for you from the
        spoil of the enemies of the Lord\u201D\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'to those who were in Bethel, those who were in Ramoth of the South,
        those who were in Jattir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'those who were in Aroer, those who were in Siphmoth, those who were
        in Eshtemoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'those who were in Rachal, those who were in the cities of the Jerahmeelites,
        those who were in the cities of the Kenites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'those who were in Hormah, those who were in Chorashan, those who
        were in Athach, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: those who were in Hebron, and to all the places where David himself
        and his men were accustomed to rove.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tragic End of Saul and His Sons'
      title: The Tragic End of Saul and His Sons
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Philistines fought against Israel; and the men of Israel
        fled from before the Philistines, and fell slain on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then the Philistines followed hard after Saul and his sons. And the
        Philistines killed Jonathan, Abinadab, and Malchishua, Saul\u2019s sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The battle became fierce against Saul. The archers hit him, and he
        was severely wounded by the archers.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Saul said to his armorbearer, \u201CDraw your sword, and thrust
        me through with it, lest these uncircumcised men come and thrust me through
        and abuse me.\u201DBut his armorbearer would not, for he was greatly afraid.
        Therefore Saul took a sword and fell on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And when his armorbearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell on
        his sword, and died with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So Saul, his three sons, his armorbearer, and all his men died together
        that same day.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when the men of Israel who were on the other side of the valley,
        and those who were on the other side of the Jordan, saw that the men of Israel
        had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they forsook the cities and
        fled; and the Philistines came and dwelt in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So it happened the next day, when the Philistines came to strip the
        slain, that they found Saul and his three sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they cut off his head and stripped off his armor, and sent word
        throughout the land of the Philistines, to proclaim it  in the temple of
        their idols and among the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then they put his armor in the temple of the Ashtoreths, and they
        fastened his body to the wall of Beth Shan.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now when the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead heard what the Philistines
        had done to Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'all the valiant men arose and traveled all night, and took the body
        of Saul and the bodies of his sons from the wall of Beth Shan; and they came
        to Jabesh and burned them there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Then they took their bones and buried them under the tamarisk tree
        at Jabesh, and fasted seven days.
      comments: []
